%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Goods%20Exports%20Decline%206.9%25%20Year-On-Year%20in%20August%20Due%20to%20Weak%20External%20Demand%3A%20Report%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F04%2F19151431%2Fimage-920.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20India%E2%80%99s%20merchandise%20exports%20continued%20to%20decline%20for%20the%20seventh%20consecutive%20month%20in%20August%2C%20dropping%20by%206.9%25%20year-on-year%20to%20%2434.48%20billion%20due%20to%20weak%20external%20demand%2C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Feconomy%2Fnews%2Ftrade-deficit-widens-to-10-month-high-in-august-exports-dip-6-9-123091501098_1.html%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Business%20Standard%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Friday%2C%20September%2015%2C%20citing%20data%20from%20the%20commerce%20department.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20business%20daily%20added%20that%20the%20government%2C%20however%2C%20expressed%20optimism%2C%20saying%20that%20exports%20were%20%E2%80%9Cstabilising%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgreenshoots%E2%80%9D%20were%20clearly%20visible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20merchandise%20trade%20deficit%2C%20or%20the%20gap%20between%20exports%20and%20imports%2C%20reached%20a%2010-month%20high%20of%20%2424.16%20billion%20in%20August.%20This%20was%20driven%20by%20higher%20crude%20oil%20prices%20and%20robust%20domestic%20demand%2C%20leading%20to%20an%20almost%2011%25%20jump%20in%20imports%20compared%20to%20the%20previous%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImports%20were%20recorded%20at%20%2458.64%20billion%20last%20month%2C%20down%205.2%25%20year-on-year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20newspaper%2C%20commerce%20secretary%20Sunil%20Barthwal%20attributed%20some%20of%20the%20contraction%20to%20a%20high%20base%20from%20the%20previous%20year%20and%20falling%20commodity%20prices%20affecting%20export%20values%2C%20although%20export%20volumes%20remained%20positive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3