mers%20logging%20in%20Idaho%20before%20moving%20to%20Los%20Angeles%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMueller%20grew%20up%20just%20100%20miles%20from%20the%20border%20of%20Canada%20in%20the%20town%20of%20Saint%20Maries%2C%20population%202%2C500.%20Passionate%20about%20science%20fiction%2C%20he%20started%20building%20rockets%20aged%2014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20a%20father%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20lumberjack%2C%20Mueller%20took%20up%20the%20chainsaw%20during%20his%20summer%20vacations%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Idaho%20in%20the%20mid-1980s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20still%20has%20%26quot%3Bthe%20rough-hewn%20look%20of%20a%20future%20lumberjack%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20Isaacson.%20But%20growing%20up%20around%20machines%20and%20tools%20also%20informed%20his%20passion%20for%20science%20and%20rocket%20building.%20%26quot%3BBeing%20hands-on%20gave%20me%20a%20feel%20for%20what%20would%20work%20and%20what%20wouldn't%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20tells%20Isaacson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20graduating%2C%20Mueller%20moved%20to%20Los%20Angeles%20to%20start%20his%20career%20in%20aerospace%2C%20getting%20a%20job%20working%20on%20aircraft%20at%20TRW%20and%20becoming%20a%20member%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rrs.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReaction%20Research%20Society%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20America's%20oldest%20amateur%20rocketry%20club.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMusk%20and%20Mueller%20devised%20SpaceX%20on%20a%20Super%20Bowl%20Sunday%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20Sunday%20in%20January%202002%2C%20Mueller%20was%20working%20on%20a%20homemade%20rocket%20in%20a%20garage%20with%20friends%20when%20he%20was%20told%20the%20internet%20millionaire%20Musk%2C%20who'd%20just%20sold%20PayPal%20to%20Ebay%20for%20%241.5%20billion%2C%20wanted%20to%20meet%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20arranged%20a%20meeting%20for%20the%20following%20weekend%2C%20which%20happened%20to%20be%20Super%20Bowl%20Sunday%2C%20at%20which%20they%20sketched%20out%20plans%20for%20the%20first%20SpaceX%20rocket.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20watched%20like%20maybe%20one%20play%2C%20because%20we%20were%20so%20engaged%20in%20talking%20about%20building%20a%20launch%20vehicle%2C%26quot%3B%20Mueller%20told%20Isaacson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlong%20with%20Chris%20Thompson%2C%20the%20trio%20set%20up%20what%20was%20known%20as%20Space%20Exploration%20Technologies%20Corporation%20before%20becoming%20SpaceX%20later%20that%20year.%20Mueller%20was%20made%20head%20of%20propulsion%20%E2%80%93%20calculating%20how%20to%20safely%20create%20enough%20thrust%20to%20get%20the%20rockets%20off%20the%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%20lucky%20that%20I%20met%20the%20right%20visionary%20and%20because%20of%20my%20passion%20for%20rocket%20engineering%20I%20was%20invited%20to%20this%20opportunity%20that%20became%20SpaceX%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20of%20the%20meeting%20at%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D8RK80QUkjKA%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2018%20commencement%20speech%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Idaho.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMueller's%20rocky%20start%20with%20Musk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMueller%20made%20a%20misstep%20when%20he%20started%20working%20at%20SpaceX.%20Not%20wanting%20to%20risk%20his%20finances%20if%20the%20venture%20failed%2C%20he%20asked%20Musk%20to%20put%20two%20years'%20worth%20of%20compensation%20into%20escrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMusk%20agreed%2C%20but%20Isaacson%20writes%20that%20this%20meant%20Musk%20considered%20%26quot%3BMueller%20an%20employee%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20cofounder%2C%20of%20SpaceX.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20cannot%20ask%20for%20two%20years%20of%20salary%20in%20escrow%20and%20consider%20yourself%20a%20cofounder%26quot%3B%20Musk%20told%20Isaacson.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20got%20to%20be%20some%20combination%20of%20inspiration%2C%20perspiration%2C%20and%20risk%20to%20be%20a%20cofounder.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Elon%20Musk%20in%202004%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65056ee0c72f090019a7f6f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EElon%20Musk%20with%20a%20SpaceX%20rocket%20in%20March%202004%20in%20El%20Segundo%2C%20Los%20Angeles.%3Cp%3EPaul%20Harris%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%26quot%3BA%20maniancal%20sense%20of%20urgency%20is%20our%20operating%20principle%26quot%3B%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20SpaceX%2C%20Mueller%20got%20the%20chance%20to%20fulfill%20his%20childhood%20dream%20of%20working%20on%20rockets.%20But%20he%20was%20also%20working%20for%20an%20%26quot%3Binsane%26quot%3B%20boss%20who%20managed%20SpaceX%20through%20aggressive%20scheduling%2C%20a%20learn-by-failing%20mantra%2C%20and%20taught%20his%20employees%20to%20never%20say%20no%20to%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20were%20negative%20or%20thought%20something%20couldn't%20be%20done%2C%20you%20were%20not%20invited%20to%20the%20next%20meeting%2C%26quot%3B%20Mueller%20recalls%20in%20Isaacson's%20biography.%20%26quot%3BHe%20just%20wanted%20people%20who%20would%20make%20things%20happen.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20presenting%20an%20already%20cut-down%20schedule%20for%20a%20Merlin%20engine%2C%20Musk%20complained%20that%20they%20had%20to%20move%20faster%2C%20per%20Isaacson's%20book.%20%26quot%3BHow%20the%20fuck%20can%20it%20take%20so%20long%3F%26quot%3B%20Musk%20asked.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20stupid.%20Cut%20it%20in%20half.%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Mueller%20told%20him%20that%20was%20impossible%2C%20he%20was%20held%20back%20after%20the%20meeting%20and%20told%20that%20if%20he%20wanted%20to%20remain%20in%20charge%20of%20engines%20he%20should%20give%20Musk%20what%20he%20asked%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20learned%20never%20to%20tell%20him%20no%2C%26quot%3B%20Mueller%20says.%20%26quot%3BJust%20say%20you're%20going%20to%20try%2C%20then%20later%20explain%20why%20if%20it%20doesn't%20work%20out%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%20the%20sense%20of%20urgency%20made%20the%20impossible%20happen%2C%20Mueller%20says%20of%20Musk's%20operational%20style%20in%20the%20biography.%20But%20it%20was%20also%20his%20biggest%20weakness%3A%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20give%20them%20a%20schedule%20that's%20physically%20impossible%2C%20engineers%20aren't%20stupid.%20You've%20demoralized%20them.%20It's%20Elon's%20biggest%20weakness.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%202014%20he%20became%20CTO%20of%20propulsion%2C%20leading%20the%20development%20of%20the%20Merlin%20rocket%20engine%20that%20powers%20the%20Falcon%209%20rocket%2C%20and%20the%20Draco%20engines%20that%20power%20the%20Dragon%20spacecraft.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20am%20very%20proud%20of%20what%20we%20have%20achieved%20at%20SpaceX%2C%26quot%3B%20Mueller%20told%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.uidaho.edu%2Fengr%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2Ftom-mueller%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Idaho%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFalcon%209%20is%2010%20for%2010!%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fhashtag%2FSpaceX%3Fsrc%3Dhash%26ref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3E%23SpaceX%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2FeRJ8pHVbg1%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2FeRJ8pHVbg1%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Tom%20Mueller%20(%40lrocket)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Flrocket%2Fstatus%2F488785858825183232%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2014%2C%202014%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Ch2%3EMueller's%20Mars%20race%20with%20Musk%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMueller%20left%20SpaceX%20in%20late%202020%20and%2C%20thanks%20to%20significant%20investor%20encouragement%20from%20the%20likes%20of%20Peter%20Thiel%2C%20founded%20his%20own%20comp