e%20composition%20of%20modern%20families.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompared%20to%201970%2C%20far%20fewer%20adults%20are%20living%20with%20a%20spouse%20and%20at%20least%20one%20child.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIt%20reflects%20how%20socioeconomic%20challenges%20are%20changing%20what%20families%20look%20like.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGone%20are%20the%20white%20picket%20fences%2C%20the%20two-and-a-half%20children%20in%20the%20suburbs%2C%20and%20married%20parents.%20The%20American%20nuclear%20family%20is%20officially%20dead%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F09%2F14%2Fthe-modern-american-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enew%20analysis%20from%20the%20Pew%20Research%20Center%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20even%20if%20some%20Americans%20haven't%20accepted%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201970%2C%20nearly%2070%25%20of%20American%20adults%20ages%2025%20to%2049%20were%20living%20with%20a%20spouse%20and%20at%20least%20one%20child.%20As%20of%202021%20%E2%80%94%20the%20most%20recent%20year%20for%20which%20they%20have%20data%20%E2%80%94%20that's%20fallen%20to%2037%25.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20other%20family%20arrangements%20have%20become%20more%20common%3A%20In%201970%2C%20essentially%20no%20one%20was%20reported%20to%20be%20cohabitating%20unmarried%20with%20kids%3B%20by%202021%2C%20that%20rose%20to%205%25.%20And%2C%20significantly%2C%2018%25%20of%20American%20adults%20were%20married%20with%20no%20kids%20in%201970.%20As%20of%202021%2C%20that's%20risen%20to%2021%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFamily%20living%20arrangements%20are%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20diverse%20in%20their%20composition%2C%26quot%3B%20Carolina%20Arag%C3%A3o%2C%20one%20of%20the%20authors%20of%20the%20Pew%20report%2C%20told%20Insider.%20While%20married%20adults%20with%20kids%20are%20still%20the%20most%20common%20family%20arrangement%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20far%20less%20common%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20past.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20makes%20sense%3A%20Americans%20are%20getting%20married%20less%2C%20and%20later%20in%20life%2C%20and%20they're%20also%20having%20fewer%20children.%20You%20can%20chalk%20some%20of%20that%20up%20to%20how%20millennials%20%E2%80%94%20and%2C%20increasingly%2C%20Gen%20Z%20%E2%80%94%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-changed-typical-american-family-structure-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Enavigating%20their%20own%20socioeconomic%20challenges%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20For%20instance%2C%20millennials%20have%20powered%20a%20rise%20in%20multigenerational%20households%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-changed-typical-american-family-structure-2019-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EInsider%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%20Pew%20finds%20that%2011%25%20of%20adults%20were%20living%20with%20other%20family%20members%20in%202021%2C%20up%20from%205%25%20in%201970.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20Census%20Bureau%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.census.gov%2Fnewsroom%2Fpress-releases%2F2022%2Famericas-families-and-living-arrangements.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520estimated%2520median%2520age%2520to%2C20.5%252C%2520respectively%252C%2520in%25201947.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20median%20age%20for%20first%20marriages%20has%20risen%20substantially%20for%20both%20men%20and%20women.%20In%201957%2C%20women%20got%20married%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20age%2020.5%3B%20in%202022%2C%20that%20was%2028.2.%20It's%20similar%20for%20men%2C%20who%20got%20married%20for%20the%20first%20time%20at%20age%2023.7%20in%201957%20and%20age%2030.1%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20who's%20getting%20married%20is%20changing%3A%20Pew%20finds%20that%2016%25%20of%20married%20American%20adults%20are%20in%20an%20interracial%20marriage%2C%20up%20from%20just%204%25%20in%201970.%20The%20percentage%20of%20same-sex%20marriages%20has%20also%20increased%20since%20it%20was%20ruled%20legal%20nationwide%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20marriage%20is%20increasingly%20becoming%20something%20that%20not%20every%20American%20seems%20to%20have%20access%20to.%20In%201970%2C%20Americans%20with%20a%20high%20school%20diploma%20were%20just%20as%20likely%20as%20Americans%20with%20at%20least%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20to%20be%20married.%20That's%20not%20true%20anymore.%20It%20also%20means%20that%20Americans%20with%20less%20education%20%E2%80%94%20along%20with%20Black%20Americans%20and%20Hispanic%20Americans%2C%20who%20have%20seen%20their%20marriage%20rates%20plunge%20%E2%80%94%20are%20missing%20out%20on%20the%20greater%20net%20worth%20and%20greater%20chance%20of%20homeownership%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.stlouisfed.org%2Fpublications%2Fin-the-balance%2F2018%2Fas-fewer-young-adults-wed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eassociated%20with%20marriage%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNowadays%2C%20what%20we%20see%20is%20that%20individuals%20who%20have%20a%20bachelor's%20degree%20are%20much%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20married%20than%20individuals%20who%20have%20a%20high%20school%20education%2C%26quot%3B%20Arag%C3%A3o%20said.%20During%20the%20time%20period%20that%20Pew%20looked%20at%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20know%20that%20socioeconomic%20inequalities%20in%20the%20United%20States%20have%20increased%2C%26quot%3B%20Arag%C3%A3o%20said%2C%20and%20that's%20%26quot%3Breflected%20in%20how%20families%20look%20like%20today.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20even%20as%20the%20American%20family%20changes%2C%20it%20doesn't%20mean%20Americans%20feel%20good%20about%20it.%20Pew%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Fsocial-trends%2F2023%2F09%2F14%2Fpublic-has-mixed-views-on-the-modern-american-family%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Efound%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Americans%20are%20pessimistic%20about%20the%20future%20of%20the%20family%20and%20marriage%2C%20although%20more%20said%20that%20having%20a%20job%20or%20career%20they%20enjoy%20is%20more%20fulfilling%20than%20having%20children%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20money%2C%20or%20being%20married.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20definitely%20still%20view%20that%20nuclear%20family%20as%20the%20most%20acceptable%20and%20ideal%20form%2C%20even%20though%20families%20are%20becoming%20more%20and%20more%20different%20and%20they're%20much%20more%20diverse%20than%20they%20were%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20Arag%C3%A3o%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAre%20you%20living%20in%20a%20nontraditional%20family%2C%20or%20putting%20off%20marriage%20or%20kids%20due%20to%20financial%20concerns%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajkaplan%40insider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cu%3Ejkaplan%40insider.com%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-marriage-family-structure-kids-over-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694856061000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6504a345916aab00192f3b02%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-marriage-family-structure-kids-over-2023-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20number%20of%20Americans%20living%20with%20a%20spouse%20and%20children%20has%20plummeted%20in%20the%20last%2050%20years.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Juliana%20Kaplan)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-marriage-family-structure-kids-over-2023-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Aid%20groups%20sound%20alarm%20in%20Libya%20as%20hopes%20fade%20for%20flood%20survivors%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694855922