me%20customers%20are%20sick%20of%20it%2C%20wondering%20when%20it's%20OK%20to%20simply%20%3Cem%3Enot%3C%2Fem%3E%20tip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20these%20days%2C%20when%20you%20make%20a%20purchase%20at%20a%20coffee%20shop%2C%20convenience%20store%2C%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-are-hesitant-to-tip-at-self-check-out-2023-5%5C%22%3Eeven%20a%20self-checkout%20kiosk%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20might%20be%20prompted%20on%20the%20checkout%20screen%20for%20a%20tip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20some%20customers%20might%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcustomers-being-asked-to-tip-everywhere-theyre-sick-of-it-2023-3%5C%22%3Eignoring%20these%20prompts%20in%20a%20bout%20of%20tipping%20fatigue%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20others%20might%20just%20be%20wondering%20what%20the%20unspoken%20rules%20are%20these%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20frustration%20is%20clear%3A%20Roughly%2066%25%20of%20US%20adults%20have%20a%20negative%20view%20of%20tipping%2C%20and%20nearly%201%20in%203%20thinking%20tipping%20culture%20has%20gotten%20out%20of%20control%2C%20according%20to%20a%20Bankrate%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bankrate.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ftipping-survey%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20are%20being%20asked%20to%20tip%20in%20contexts%20where%20they%20have%20not%20traditionally%20been%20asked%20to%20tip%2C%20and%20they're%20being%20asked%20to%20tip%20larger%20amounts%20in%20those%20occupations%20where%20there%20are%20used%20to%20leaving%20tips%20%E2%80%94%20and%20it's%20that%20felt%20social%20pressure%20that's%20irritating%20people%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20tipping%20expert%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.tippingresearch.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMichael%20Lynn%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20consumer%20behavior%20and%20marketing%20at%20the%20Cornell%20University%20School%20of%20Hotel%20Administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInsider%20talked%20to%20tipping%20and%20etiquette%20experts%20to%20figure%20out%20exactly%20when%20you%20can%20forgo%20a%20tip%20without%20making%20a%20faux%20pas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E'Take%20it%20as%20a%20suggestion%2C%20not%20an%20obligation'%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20pandemic%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fexperts-on-how-much-to-tip-at-restaurants-during-pandemic-2020-7%5C%22%3Epeople%20began%20tipping%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20generously%2C%20which%20set%20a%20new%20precedent%20for%20how%20much%20some%20workers%20expected%20to%20earn%20from%20tips.%20Now%2C%20as%20the%20world%20adjusts%20to%20a%20post-pandemic%20normal%2C%20some%20businesses%20have%20continued%20relying%20on%20tips%20to%20bolster%20their%20workers'%20wages.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ubiquity%20of%20checkout%20stations%20with%20tip%20prompts%20also%20comes%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpowering-the-pos-how-providers-building-cost-effective-omnichannel-solutions-2023-april%5C%22%3Egrowing%20number%20of%20businesses%20that%20have%20adopted%20consumer-facing%20point-of-sale%20systems%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20Toast%20or%20Square%2C%20over%20the%20past%20several%20years.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThomas%20Farley%2C%20a%20New%20York-based%20etiquette%20expert%20known%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmister-manners.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMister%20Manners%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20Insider%20that%20those%20factors%20don't%20necessarily%20translate%20into%20the%20expectation%20that%20customers%20should%20also%20tip%20more.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20because%20the%20screen%20in%20these%20point-of-purchase%20or%20over-the-counter-type%20transactions%20provides%20you%20with%20that%20suggestion%2C%20you%20should%20take%20it%20as%20merely%20that%3A%20a%20suggestion%20and%20not%20an%20obligation%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EYou%20can%20skip%20the%20tip%20at%20self-checkout%20kiosks%20...%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20know%20to%20tip%20for%20service%20we%20receive%2C%20but%20what%20if%20we're%20providing%20the%20service%20ourselves%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20thing%20that%20really%20just%20blows%20my%20mind%20is%20that%20people%20are%20being%20asked%20to%20tip%20for%20self-service%20kiosk%20and%20checkout%20lines%2C%26quot%3B%20Lynn%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20one%20that%20surprises%20me%20the%20most%20because%20it's%20not%20clear%20who's%20receiving%20those%20tips.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20ringing%20up%20your%20own%20items%2C%20don't%20worry%20about%20tipping%2C%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E...%20and%20skip%20tipping%20for%20takeout%20and%20counter%20service%2C%20like%20coffee%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20picking%20up%20your%20own%20food%2C%20you%20can%20likely%20skip%20the%20tip%2C%20too.%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-much-to-tip-food-delivery-driver-doordash-ubereats-2023-7%5C%22%3EFood%20delivery%2C%20of%20course%2C%20is%20different%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20tips%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20don't%20want%20to%20leave%20a%20tip%20for%20your%20takeout%20order%2C%20it's%20just%20sitting%20there%20on%20the%20counter%20and%20you%20grab%20it%2C%20you've%20already%20paid%20for%20it%20and%20you're%20out%2C%20you're%20just%20gonna%20grab%20it%20and%20go%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20etiquette%20expert%20Avery%20Johnson%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.southernacademyofetiquette.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Southern%20Academy%20of%20Etiquette.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Still%2C%20she%20notes%20you%20can%20tip%2010%25%20or%20more%20on%20carryout%20if%20you%20had%20special%20requests%2C%20like%20extras%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELynn%20also%20skips%20the%20tip%20on%20takeout%20%E2%80%94%20and%20even%20in%20counter-service%20situations%2C%20like%20getting%20a%20coffee%20and%20a%20pastry%20at%20a%20coffee%20shop.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EDon't%20feel%20pressured%20to%20tip%20for%20a%20sweatshirt%20you%20just%20bought%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETip%20prompts%20that%20pop%20up%20when%20you're%20making%20retail%20purchases%20are%20where%20the%20rules%20of%20tipping%20etiquette%20might%20get%20a%20little%20blurry%2C%20Farley%20said.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3ESay%20you%20landed%20tickets%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fhow-taylor-swift-eras-tour-got-into-movie-theaters-amc-2023-9%5C%22%3Esee%20the%20biggest%20concert%20of%20the%20year%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20you%20want%20to%20buy%20a%20%24100%20sweatshirt%20to%20commemorate%20the%20experience.%20You%20pay%20a%20visit%20to%20the%20stand%20selling%20concert%20merch%20where%20the%20salesperson%20needs%20to%20pull%20down%20the%20sweatshirt%20you%20picked%20from%20a%20rack%20with%20a%20pole.%20When%20you%20go%20to%20check%20out%2C%20the%20screen%20prompts%20you%20for%20a%20tip%20on%20the%20transaction.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECustomers%20who%20have%20never%20tipped%20for%20this%20type%20of%20transaction%20before%20might%20wonder%20if%20they%20should%20fork%20out%20a%20few%20more%20dollars%20here.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarley%20said%20that%20even%20in%20these%20types%20of%20scenarios%2C%20customers%20aren't%20expected%20to%20tip.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20challenging%20to%20have%20a%20transaction%2C%20especially%20if%20somebody%20smiles%2C%20and%20they're%20pleasant%2C%20and%2C%20you%20know%2C%20they%2C%20provide%20nice%20service%2C%20but%20there%20is%20still%20no%20obligation%20to%20do%20so%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%A6%20or%20a%20tipping%20on%20meal%20for%20which%20you%20already%20paid%20gratuity%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFarley%20said%20the%20most%20unexpected%20tip%20request%20he's%20ever%20received%20was%20at%20a%20sit-down%20restaurant%20where%20the%20menu%20had%20already%20indicated%20that%20a%20standard%20gratuity%20fee%20of%2020%25%20would%20be%20included%20in%20the%20bill.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20server%20handed%20Farley%20the%20final%20bill%2C%20though%2C%20he%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20prompt%20for%20another%2020%25%20tip%20by%20the%20card%20reader.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20was%20very%20confused%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%20When%20he%20asked%20the%20waiter%20why%20there%20was%20a%20second%20charge%2C%20he%20said%20the%20server%20told%20him%20the%2020%25%20gratuity%20charge%20was%20for%20the%20whole%20staff%20to%20split%2C%20but%2020%25%20prompt%20on%20the%20card%20reader%20was%20specifically%20for%20his%20service%20that%20night.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%26quot%3BThe%20service%20was%20not%2040%25%20service%2C%20the%20service%20was%2020%25%20service%2C%20but%20I%20was%20stuck%20into%20paying%2040%25%2C%26quot%3B%20Farley%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20worried%20you%20might%20find%20yourself%20in%20this%20situation%2C%20Farley%20said%20you%20can%20ask%20the%20restaurant%20to%20waive%20the%20initial%20gratuity%20fee.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20feel%20strongly%20about%20it%2C%20and%20you%20feel%20that%20burden%20shouldn't%20be%20on%20you%2C%20restaurant%20owners%20that%20I've%20encountered%2C%20and%20have%20read%20interviews%20with%2C%20will%20say%20that%20for%20any%20consumers%20that%20push%20back%20and%20request%20that%20that%20charge%20be%20removed%2C%20they%20will%20comply.%26quot%3B%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EOtherwise%2C%20he%20suggested%20%26quot%3Bdo%20your%20homework%26quot%3B%20on%20a%20restaurant's%20tipping%20policy%2C%20so%20you%20can%20avoid%20a%20potentially%20awkward%20encounter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftipping-restaurant-takeout-coffee-checkout-should-i-tip-etiquette-tips-2023-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694854681000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6504bec45f9f9c0019b43f0d%3Ffor