%20speculation.%20The%20media%20has%20been%20approaching%20the%20subject%20like%20the%20proverbial%20blind%20men%20and%20an%20elephant.%20An%20all-party%20pre-session%20meet%20to%20discuss%20the%20agenda%20is%20scheduled%20on%20Sunday.%20However%2C%20with%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20regime's%20penchant%20for%20setting%20the%20pigeon%20among%20cats%2C%20conjectures%20persist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeptember%2018%2C%20the%20day%20the%20session%20starts%2C%20is%20the%20anniversary%20of%20the%20day%20in%201949%20when%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%20of%20India%20adopted%20clause%201%20of%20Article%201%3A%20%26quot%3BIndia%20that%20is%20Bharat%20shall%20be%20a%20Union%20of%20States%26quot%3B.%20As%20many%20as%20222%20amendments%20were%20moved%20before%20this%20was%20adopted.%20Amendment%20number%20130%2C%20moved%20by%20HV%20Kamath%2C%20supported%20by%20Seth%20Govind%20Das%20and%20Kamlapati%20Tripathi%2C%20debated%20whether%20Dr%20BR%20Ambedkar's%20formulation%20of%20%26quot%3BIndia%20that%20is%20Bharat%26quot%3B%20ought%20to%20be%20reworded%20as%20%26quot%3BBharat%20that%20is%20India%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeth%20Govind%20Das%20cited%20Chinese%20traveller%20Huen%20Tsang%2C%20who%20had%20referred%20to%20%26quot%3BBharat%26quot%3B.%20Tripathi%20traced%20the%20name%20Bharat%20to%20Rig%20Ved.%20After%20animated%20discussion%20the%20amendment%20was%20negated.%20September%2018%2C%201949%20was%20a%20Sunday.%20The%20House%20met%20thereafter%20on%20October%206%20to%20continue%20formulating%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20use%20of%20Bharat%20in%20official%20communication%20in%20G20%2C%20the%20discussion%20on%2075%20years%20of%20our%20democracy%20during%20the%20Special%20Session%20will%20be%20riveting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOpinion%20on%20%26quot%3BBharat%26quot%3B%20is%20sharply%20divided%20even%20today.%20On%20April%203%2C%201984%2C%20speaking%20to%20the%20only%20Indian%20who%20has%20thus%20far%20been%20to%20space%2C%20Squadron%20Leader%20Rakesh%20Sharma%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20had%20queried%2C%20%26quot%3BUpar%20se%20Bharat%20kaisa%20dikhta%20hai%20aapko%3F%26quot%3B%20He%20replied%20in%20Urdu%3A%26quot%3BSaare%20Jahan%20se%20achccha%26quot%3B.%20After%20Chandrayaan's%20success%2C%20as%20India%20plans%20a%20manned%20space%20mission%2C%20this%20interaction%20and%20the%20use%20of%20%26quot%3BBharat%26quot%3B%20assumes%20significance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGanesh%20Chaturthi%2C%20September%2019%2C%20the%20second%20day%20of%20the%20session%2C%20is%20slated%20for%20shifting%20the%20working%20of%20the%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20from%20the%20British-built%20circular%20edifice%20to%20the%20triangular%20new%20Parliament%20House%2C%20ushering%20a%20new%20era%20in%20our%20parliamentary%20democracy.%20This%20magnificent%20structure%20will%20thereafter%20be%20the%20venue%20for%20a%20conclave%20of%20G20%20nations'%20legislatures%20in%20mid-October.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20May%2028%2C%20the%20ninth%20anniversary%20of%20Narendra%20Modi's%20regime%2C%20the%20new%20parliament%20building%20was%20inaugurated.%20Seers%20from%20temples%20in%20southern%20India%20worshipped%20the%20Sengol%20(sceptre)%20with%20which%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20had%20symbolically%20accepted%20power%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20Independence%2C%20and%20which%20was%20resurrected%20from%20a%20museum%20in%20Allahabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EModi%2C%20accompanied%20by%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%2C%20carried%20the%20Sengol%20and%20placed%20it%20on%20the%20right%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker's%20chair%2C%20symbolising%20the%20Raajdand%20(sceptre)%20of%20India's%20democracy.%20The%20Sengol%2C%20designed%20on%20a%20Chola%20era%20model%2C%20was%20suggested%20by%20new%20India's%20first%20Indian%20Head%20of%20State%2C%20Chakravarti%20Rajagopalachari%2C%20as%20the%20symbol%20of%20transfer%20of%20power%20in%201947.%20Nehru%20received%20it%20from%20seers%20prior%20to%20delivering%20his%20%26quot%3BTryst%20with%20Destiny%26quot%3B%20midnight%20clarion.%20It%20disappeared%20from%20the%20public%20eye%20thereafter.%20It%20had%20been%20packed%20and%20stored%20in%20a%20museum%20in%20Allahabad%20along%20with%20Nehru's%20personal%20artefacts%20after%20his%20death%20in%201964.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20event%20serenaded%20the%20Ninth%20City%20of%20Delhi-successor%20to%20the%20British-built%20Lutyens'%20Delhi%2C%20known%20as%20New%20Delhi%2C%20which%20was%20the%20eighth%20after%20Qutubuddin%20Aibak's%20Mehrauli%2C%20Siri%2C%20Tughlaqbad%2C%20Jehapanah%2C%20Firozabad%2C%20Sher%20Shah%20Suri's%20settlements%20around%20Purana%20Quila%20and%20Shahjahanabad%20in%20recorded%20history(%20Delhi's%20history%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20Indraprastha%20of%20the%20Mahabharat%20era).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%202014%2C%20the%20task%20of%20eclipsing%20the%20British-era%20heritage%20of%20the%20city%20and%20the%20redevelopment%20of%20the%20Central%20Vista%2C%20the%20seat%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India%2C%20has%20been%20handled%20by%20Housing%20and%20Urban%20Affairs%20Minister%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Puri.%20The%20Central%20Vista%20now%20wears%20a%20festive%20look%3B%20the%20footfall%20of%20local%20visitors%20and%20tourists%20has%20increased%20manifold.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20central%20avenue%20named%20Kingsway%20by%20Lutyens%2C%20changed%20to%20Rajpath%20in%201947%3B%20it%20was%20renamed%20Kartavya%20Path%20by%20Modi%20in%20September%202022.%20This%20avenue%20hosts%20the%20Republic%20Day%20parade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENear%20the%20Kartavya%20Path%2C%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20central%20government%20in%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru%20and%20Lal%20Bahadur%20Shastri-era%20buildings%2C%20though%20majestic%2C%20are%20overcrowded%20and%20show%20signs%20of%20wear-and-tear.%20They%20are%20being%20replaced%20by%20state-of-the-art%20green%20buildings.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20offices%20were%20housed%20in%20temporary%20hutments%20built%20during%20World%20War%20II%20when%20New%20Delhi%20was%20the%20Theatre%20Command%20for%20the%20East%20and%20Far%20East.%20These%20dingy%2C%20leaky%2C%20damp%2C%20hutments%20served%20as%20government%20offices%20from%201947%2C%20until%20Modi%20planned%20New%20Delhi's%20revamp.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EVanijya%20Bhavan%2C%20housing%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Commerce%20and%20Janganana%20Bhavan%2C%20the%20office%20of%20the%20census%20commissioner%2C%20and%20the%20new%20offices%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defence%20now%20dot%20the%20vista%20around%20India%20Gate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20redevelopment%20project%20is%20completed%2C%20an%20underground%20circular%20railway%20will%20connect%20all%20government%20buildings%2C%20reducing%20the%20dependence%20on%20staff%20cars.%20Green%20technology%20is%20being%20harnessed%20not%20only%20in%20the%20buildings%20but%20also%20in%20providing%20an%20omnibus%20environment-friendly%20paradigm%20to%20the%20headquarters%20of%20the%20Government%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20a%20new%20building%20for%20parliament%20and%20office%20blocks%2C%20new%20residence%20complexes%20for%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20and%20Vice%20President%20of%20India%20are%20under%20construction.%20Teen%20Murti%20Bhavan%2C%20which%20served%20as%20Jawaharlal%20Nehru's%20home%2C%20was%20converted%20into%20a%20museum%20in%20his%20name%20after%20his%20death%20in%201964.%20The%20PM%20house%20was%20located%20and%20relocated%20several%20times%20thereafter.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ensure%20that%20no%20bungalows%20are%20converted%20into%20museums%20for%20remembering%20iconic%20PMs%20henceforth%2C%20a%20memorial%20complex%20for%20all%20Prime%20Ministers%2C%20past%20and%20future%2C%20has%20been%20set%20up%20in%20the%20Teen%20Murti%20complex%20by%20the%20present%20regime.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20parliament%20project%20will%20also%20seat%20an%20expanded%20parliament%20(Lok%20Sabha%20will%20have%20888%20seats%20as%20against%20the%20present%20strength%20of%20542%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha%20is%20projected%20at%20300%2B%2C%2075%20more%20than%20present%20strength).%20The%20delimitation%20of%20seats%20will%20be%20done%20after%20the%20next%20census%2C%20which%20has%20been%20delayed%20due%20to%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndividual%20offices%20will%20not%20be%20provided%20to%20MPs-somewhat%20like%20the%20US%20Capitol%20-%20and%20professional%20facilities%20will%20be%20provided%20to%20elected%20representatives%20where%20they%20can%20interact%20with%20their%20constituents.Australia%2C%20Germany%2C%20abd%20UK%20are%20other%20countries%20where%20office%20accommodation%20and%20work%20facility%20is%20extended%20to%20MPs.%20A%20new%20paradigm%20for%20parliament%20is%20in%20the%20offing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20negative%20feature%20of%20the%20new%20regimen%20will%20be%20the%20absence%20of%20a%20Central%20Hall%20of%20Parliament%2C%20where%20the%20accredited%20media%20freely%20interacted%20with%20those%20who%20stride%20the%20corridors%20of%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20large%20part%20of%20Lutyens'%20Delhi%2C%20which%20may%20now%20well%20be%20called%20Modi's%20Delhi%2C%20is%20devoted%20to%20massive%20bungalows%20and%20multi-storied%20complexes%20to%20provide%20housing%20for%20MPs.%20In%20the%20days%20of%20the%20Central%20Legislative%20Assembly%20and%20the%20Constituent%20Assembly%2C%20members%20were%20mainly%20accommodated%20in%20transit%20accommodation%20in%20Janpath%20(then%20called%20Queensway).%20With%20the%20number%20of%20MPs%20projected%20to%20grow%20after%20the%20next%20delimitation%20of%20seats%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20such%20housing%20will%20grow%20manifold.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Houses%20of%20Parliament%20meet%20for%20around%20100%20days%20in%20a%20year.%20MPs%20are%20needed%20in%20the%20capital%20for%20another%2030-40%20days%20for%20meetings%20of%20parliamentary%20committees.%20Is%20there%20a%20need%20to%20provide%20plush%20accommodation%20with%20attendant%20freebies%20to%20MPs%20whose%20presence%20is%20mandated%20in%20Delhi%20for%20less%20than%2040%20per%20cent%20of%20days%20in%20a%20year%3F%20In%20the%20initial%20years%20of%20the%20Republic%20most%20MPs%20kept%20their%20families%20in%20their%20constituencies.%20Their%20children%20attended%20local%20educational%20institutions.%20The%20present%20Delhi-isation%20of%20MPs%20ought%20to%20be%20reversed.%20This%20may%20be%20considered%20the%20next%20step%20in%20the%20slew%20of%20reforms%20unleashed%20by%20Modi%20since%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Shubhabrata%20Bhattacharya%20is%20a%20retired%20Editor%20and%20a%20public%20affairs%20commentator)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694852580000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2Fbs8udj88_pm-modi-ndtv-650_650x400_14_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-cheerio-india-namaste-bharat-4395225%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20beginning%20Monday%20has%20generated%20much%20speculation.%20The%20media%20has%20been%20approaching%20the%20subject%20like%20the%20proverbial%20blind%20men%20and%20an%20elephant.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-cheerio-india-namaste-bharat-4395225%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-cheerio-india-namaste-bharat-4395225%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fopinion-cheerio-india-namaste-bharat-4395225%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Amid%20Indian%20Army's%20Fight%20With%20Terrorists%2C%20Interference%20From%20%26quot%3BPak%20Post%26quot%3B%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20Army%20today%20shot%20dead%20three%20terrorists%20who%20tried%20to%20cross%20the%20Line%20of%20Control%20(LoC)%20from%20Pakistan-occupied%20Kashmir%20into%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir's%20Uri%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bodies%20of%20two%20terrorists%20have%20been%20recovered%2C%20the%20Indian%20Army's%20Chinar%20Corps%