ve%20been%20strained%20over%20increasing%20Khalistani%20activities.%20Following%20a%20meeting%20between%20PM%20Modi%20and%20Mr%20Trudeau%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20G20%2C%20India%20issued%20a%20strongly-worded%20statement%20expressing%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20concerns%26quot%3B%20about%20the%20continuous%20%26quot%3Banti-India%20activities%26quot%3B%20by%20extremist%20elements%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ministry%20of%20External%20Affairs%20said%20PM%20Modi%20had%20conveyed%20in%20the%20meeting%20that%20extremist%20elements%20are%20%26quot%3Bpromoting%20secessionism%20and%20inciting%20violence%26quot%3B%20against%20Indian%20diplomats%2C%20damaging%20diplomatic%20premises%2C%20and%20threatening%20the%20Indian%20community%20in%20Canada%20and%20their%20places%20of%20worship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20nexus%20of%20such%20forces%20with%20organized%20crime%2C%20drug%20syndicates%20and%20human%20trafficking%20should%20be%20a%20concern%20for%20Canada%20as%20well.%20It%20is%20essential%20for%20the%20two%20countries%20to%20cooperate%20in%20dealing%20with%20such%20threats%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20whether%20Khlistani%20activities%20and%20%26quot%3Bforeign%20interference%26quot%3B%20were%20discussed%20in%20the%20meeting%2C%20Justin%20Trudeau%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fafter-canada-pm-justin-trudeaus-foreign-interference-comment-indias-strong-reaction-4378716%5C%22%3Etold%20reporters%3C%2Fa%3E%20Canada%20will%20always%20defend%20freedom%20of%20expression%2C%20freedom%20of%20conscience%2C%20and%20freedom%20of%20peaceful%20protest%2C%20%26quot%3Band%20it%20is%20extremely%20important%20to%20us%26quot%3B.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20same%20time%2C%20we%20are%20always%20there%20to%20prevent%20violence%20and%20push%20back%20against%20hatred%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20had%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20the%20actions%20of%20the%20few%20do%20not%20represent%20the%20entire%20community%20or%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20last%20year%20served%20a%20demarche%20to%20the%20Canadian%20government%2C%20asking%20it%20to%20stop%20the%20so-called%20Khalistan%20referendum%20organised%20by%20a%20proscribed%20organisation%20in%20Ontario.%20The%20Centre%20asked%20the%20Canadian%20government%20to%20act%20against%20those%20who%20promote%20terror%20and%20violence%20against%20the%20largest%20democracy%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBanned%20organisation%20Sikhs%20for%20Justice%2C%20headed%20by%20designated%20terrorist%20Gurpatwant%20Singh%20Pannun%2C%20held%20the%20Khalistan%20referendum%20this%20week%2C%20on%20September%2010%2C%20at%20a%20gurdwara%20in%20British%20Columbia%2C%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAhead%20of%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Canadian%20Prime%20Minister%20Justin%20Trudeau's%20government%20had%20last%20month%20requested%20a%20%26quot%3Bpause%26quot%3B%20on%20trade%20talks%20with%20India%2C%20Bloomberg%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fcanada-pauses-trade-talks-with-india-ahead-of-g-20-summit-4350536%5C%22%3Ehad%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20though%20no%20reason%20was%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndia%20and%20Canada%20had%20first%20launched%20negotiations%20for%20a%20trade%20deal%2013%20years%20ago%20in%202010.%20After%20a%20lull%20of%20almost%205%20years%2C%20the%20talks%20restarted%20in%202022%20with%20renegotiations%20on%20a%20Comprehensive%20Economic%20Partnership%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20half%20a%20dozen%20rounds%20of%20talks%20have%20been%20held%20between%20the%20countries%20on%20the%20trade%20pact%20so%20far.%20In%20March%202022%2C%20the%20two%20countries%20re-launched%20negotiations%20for%20an%20interim%20agreement-Early%20Progress%20Trade%20Agreement%20(EPTA).%20In%20such%20agreements%2C%20two%20countries%20significantly%20reduce%20or%20eliminate%20duties%20on%20the%20maximum%20number%20of%20goods%20traded%20between%20them.%20Norms%20are%20also%20liberalised%20to%2