sted%20in%20the%20past%20that%20his%20government%20does%20better%20than%20Manmohan%20Singh%20on%20inflation.%20But%20Modi%20was%20blessed%20with%20falling%20oil%2C%20food%20and%20metal%20prices%20in%20the%20years%20after%202014%2C%20which%20moderated%20overall%20inflation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20honeymoon%20with%20low%20to%20moderate%20inflation%20is%20all%20but%20over%20and%20the%20stickiness%20in%20food%20inflation%20is%20worrying%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20a%20great%20deal%20as%20several%20state%20elections%20draw%20closer%2C%20along%20with%20the%20general%20elections%20next%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJust%20as%20food%20inflation%20had%20peaked%20in%20the%20second%20half%20of%202013%2C%20the%20trend%20appears%20to%20be%20repeating%20in%202023.%20July%20and%20August%20have%20seen%20double-digit%20food%20inflation%2C%20as%20India%20suffered%20an%2011%25%20monsoon%20deficit%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20eight%20years.%20Inflationary%20expectations%20are%20clearly%20on%20the%20rise%2C%20as%20the%20government%20imposes%20export%20curbs%20on%20a%20range%20of%20food%20items.%20Prices%20of%20milk%2C%20pulses%20and%20edible%20oil%20have%20generally%20been%20structurally%20on%20the%20higher%20side%20for%20quite%20some%20time%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIndeed%2C%20if%20food%20inflation%20proves%20to%20be%20sticky%20in%20the%20months%20ahead%2C%20it%20will%20raise%20political%20headwinds%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20and%20the%20BJP%20during%20the%20crucial%20assembly%20elections%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Telangana%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%20The%20BJP%20knows%20that%20high%20energy%20prices%2C%20especially%20that%20of%20cooking%20gas%2C%20hurt%20the%20party%20badly%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20and%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Flpg-price-cut-modis-rakhi-gift-ends-up-drawing-attention-to-inflation%5C%22%3Ecut%20LPG%20prices%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20Rs%20200%20recently.%20But%20prices%20of%20LPG%2C%20diesel%20and%20petrol%20remain%20quite%20high.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20inflationary%20expectations%20build%20up%20in%20the%20economy%2C%20it%20is%20very%20difficult%20to%20put%20the%20genie%20back%20in%20the%20bottle.%20The%20Ukraine%20war%20had%20created%20the%20first%20round%20of%20very%20high%20inflationary%20expectations%20last%20year.%20Both%20food%20and%20energy%20prices%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fen%2FBlogs%2FArticles%2F2022%2F12%2F09%2Fglobal-food-prices-to-remain-elevated-amid-war-costly-energy-la-nina%5C%22%3Esoared%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20there%20was%20an%20unprecedented%20spike%20in%20global%20inflation.%20The%20advanced%20economies%20were%20hit%20hard%20and%20are%20still%20grappling%20with%20high%20inflation%20via%20blunt%20monetary%20policy%20tools.%20It%20may%20take%20a%20while%20for%20global%20inflation%20to%20flag%20and%20India%20cannot%20escape%20the%20overall%20trend%20of%20higher%20inflation%20and%20lower%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20there%20seems%20to%20be%20some%20recovery%20(contested%20by%20economists%20like%20Ashoka%20Mody)%20in%20the%20April-June%20quarter%2C%20the%20reality%20is%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20has%20grown%20annually%20only%20about%203.5%25%20for%20four%20years%20from%202019-20%20to%202022-23.%20So%20incomes%20have%20not%20really%20recovered%20significantly%20and%20inflationary%20expectations%20are%20getting%20entrenched%20even%20before%20a%20full%20recovery%20is%20underway.%20There%20is%20ample%20evidence%20from%20consumption%20patterns%20that%20the%20bottom%2070%25%20of%20the%20population%2C%20whose%20incomes%20were%20hit%20badly%20by%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20have%20not%20recovered%20yet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2015%2C%20Mallikarjun%20Kharge%20told%20the%20prime%20minister%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F6b8472bd-6f83-4d2b-be0a-f5a9ea5f5a32%3Fj%3DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%5C%22%20data-saferedirecturl%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.google.com%2Furl%3Fq%3Dhttps%3A%2F%2Fsubstack.com%2Fredirect%2F6b8472bd-6f83-4d2b-be0a-f5a9ea5f5a32%3Fj%253DeyJ1IjoiaHpuMnUifQ.MQOquijPBw98XVYBc9m195DW7Qx9ruSvngQYE7EwHGg%26amp%3Bsource%3Dgmail%26amp%3Bust%3D1694926238549000%26amp%3Busg%3DAOvVaw35hMbWYBgVYab32NZPm15e%5C%22%3Estop%20diversionary%20tactics%20and%20focus%20on%20inflation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20because%20the%2020%25%20poorest%20Indians%20are%20bearing%20the%20brunt%20of%20the%20problem%2C%20brought%20on%20by%20the%20%E2%80%9Cgrand%20loot%E2%80%9D%20conducted%20by%20his%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20nationwide%20survey%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20shows%20that%20people%20expect%20prices%20to%20remain%20high%20and%20even%20their%20expectation%20of%20future%20income%20growth%20is%20relatively%20low.%20This%20reflects%20the%20broader%20sentiment%2C%20even%20as%20self-congratulatory%20claims%20of%20India%20being%20a%20beacon%20of%20global%20growth%20abound.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20can%E2%80%99t%20help%20but%20feel%20that%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%2C%20heady%20with%20the%20G20%20success%2C%20is%20in%20a%20mood%20to%20launch%20a%20campaign%20like%20India%20Shining%2C%20which%20his%20mentor%20L.K.%20Advani%20had%20unleashed%20in%202003%20on%20the%20back%20of%20an%20incipient%20economic%20recovery.%20Is%20the%20BJP%20again%20creating%20a%20bubble%20via%20its%20own%20self-seeking%20narrative%3F%20Of%20course%2C%20the%20India%20of%202023%20is%20not%20the%20country%20it%20was%20in%202003.%20Today%2C%20significant%20sections%20of%20voters%20seem%20to%20be%20willing%20to%20suffer%20a%20great%20deal%20of%20hardship%20before%20the%20promised%20entry%20into%20%E2%80%98Amrit%20Kaal%E2%80%99%20(era%20of%20great%20prosperity).%20But%20equally%2C%20voters%20tend%20to%20change%20their%20minds%20overnight%2C%20and%20they%20will%20keep%20political%20parties%20on%20tenterhooks%20in%20the%20months%20ahead.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694843789000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F04%2F08200712%2FScreen-Shot-2020-04-08-at-8.06.53-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwill-voters-wait-hungrily-for-amrit-kaal-or-will-food-inflation-decide-the-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Prime%20Minister%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20honeymoon%20with%20low%20to%20moderate%20inflation%20is%20all%20but%20over%20and%20the%20stickiness%20in%20food%20inflation%20is%20worrying%20the%20BJP%20a%20great%20deal%20as%20several%20state%20elections%20draw%20closer%2C%20along%20with%20the%20general%20elections%20next%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwill-voters-wait-hungrily-for-amrit-kaal-or-will-food-inflation-decide-the-elections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rishi%20Sunak's%20Last-Ditch%20Plan%20To%20Save%20His%20Job%3A%20Don't%20Look%20Back%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EMuch%20of%20Westminster%20sniggered%20earlier%20this%20month%20when%20Rishi%20Sunak%20branded%20Keir%20Starmer%20%26quot%3BCaptain%20Hindsight.%26quot%3B%20But%20the%20meme-ready%20moniker%20gives%20away%20more%20than%20a%20little%20about%20the%20UK%20prime%20minister's%20plan%20to%20save%20his%20job%3A%20Don't%20look%20back.%20Barrel%20ahead.%20Hope%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPainting%20the%20Labour%20leader%20as%20backward-looking%20and%20opportunistic%20was%20among%20the%20tactics%20discussed%20this%20month%20during%20high-level%20strategy%20meetings%20at%20Conservative%20Party%20headquarters%2C%20according%20to%20people%20briefed%20on%20the%20deliberations.%20The%20idea%20is%20to%20draw%20a%20contrast%20between%20Mr%20Sunak%2C%2043%2C%20and%20his%2061-year-old%20rival%2C%20while%20attempting%20to%20wave%20away%20efforts%20to%20blame%20the%20premier%20for%20the%20Tories'%20record%20on%20public%20services%20and%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDredging%20up%20Mr%20Sunak's%20decisions%20to%20put%20off%20school%20repairs%3F%20Twenty-20%20hindsight.%20Seizing%20on%20a%20terrorism%20suspect's%20escape%20to%20raise%20questions%20about%20prison%20funding%3F%20An%20attempt%20to%20score%20cheap%20points.%20%26quot%3BThis%20is%20exactly%20the%20kind%20of%20political%20opportunism%20that%20we've%20come%20to%20expect%20from%20Captain%20Hindsight%20over%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Sunak%20shot%20at%20Starmer%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20this%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Sunak's%20strategists%20believe%20that%20getting%20voters%20to%20focus%20on%20who's%20best-placed%20to%20lead%20Britain%20over%20the%20next%20five%20to%2010%20years%20is%20their%20best%20hope%20for%20avoiding%20a%20defeat%20in%20an%20election%20expected%20to%20be%20held%20in%20November%202024.%20The%20aim%20is%20to%20portray%20Mr%20Sunak%20as%20more%20positive%2C%20dynamic%20and%20ambitious%2C%20better%20equipped%20to%20address%20new%20challenges%20such%20as%20the%20switch%20to%20electric%20vehicles%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%2C%20the%20people%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20that%20end%2C%20Mr%20Sunak%20and%20his%20top%20political%20aides%20have%20been%20focused%20on%20crafting%20bolder%20policy%20proposals%20to%20roll%20out%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20designed%20to%20present%20a%20forward-looking%20vision%20for%20voters.%20The%20hope%20is%20that%20the%20strategy%20will%20reinforce%20a%20common%20criticism%20of%20Starmer%2C%20that%20he's%20cautious%20and%20uninspiring%2C%20and%20chip%20away%20at%20Labour's%20roughly%2020-point%20lead%20in%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMr%20Sunak's%20aides%20have%20drawn%20encouragement%20from%20the%20analysis%20of%20James%20Johnson%2C%20co-founder%20of%20pollster%20JL%20Partners%2C%20who%20has%20seen%20negative%20views%20of%20Starmer%20come%20up%20in%20focus%20groups%20of%20key%20voters%20in%20recent%20weeks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTwo%20factors%20mean%20that%2C%20though%20it%20is%20clearly%20Advantage%20Labour%20at%20the%20moment%2C%20the%20next%20election%20is%20still%20up%20for%20grabs%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Johnson%2C%20a%20former%20aide%20to%20ex-premier%20Theresa%20May.%20%26quot%3BOne%2C%20the%20extreme%20volatility%20of%20the%20electorate%2C%20which%20is%20more%20likely%20to%20change%20its%20mind%20than%20ever%20before.%20Two%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20Starmer%20is%20still%20viewed%20miserably%20by%20the%20swing%20voters%20that%20matter%20most.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStrategic%20Shift%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20requires%20a%20strategic%20shift%20by%20Mr%20Sunak's%20team%2C%20who%20had%20largely%20seen%20their%20job%20as%20mitigating%20the%20scale%20of%20an%20inevitable%20defeat%20since%20taking%20over%20after%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Liz%20Truss's%20brief%20and%20chaotic%20tenure%20almost%20a%20year%20ago.%20Since%20then%2C%20Mr%20Sunak%20has%20largely%20stuck%20to%20his%20so-called%20five%20pledges%20-%20including%20halving%20inflation%20and%20growing%20the%20economy%20-%20and%20resisted%20calls%20for%20a%20broader%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20some%20inside%20No.%2010%20are%20arguing%20that%20they%20need%20a%20bigger%20strategy%20to%20win.%20One%20official%20said%20they%20were%20clear-eyed%20that%20the%20odds%20favored%20Labour%2C%20but%20argued%20that%20the%20realm%20of%20possibility%20included%20a%20surprise%20victory%20and%20not%20just%20a%20respectable%20loss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20with%20this%20blue-skies%20plan%20is%20that%20assumes%20it%20can%20counteract%20the%20electorate's%20desire%20for%20change%20after%2013%20years%20of%20Conservative%20rule.%20The%20party%20lost%20more%20than%201%2C000%20seats%20local%20elections%20in%20May%20and%20was%20defeated%20in%20two%20bellwhether%20parliamentary%20contests%20in%20July%2C%20even%20it%20narrowly%20held%20the%20former%20seat%20of%20ex-Prime%20Minister%20Boris%20Johnson.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarmer%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20increasingly%20looks%20like%20a%20prime%20minister-in-waiting%2C%20visiting%20The%20Hague%20this%20week%20to%20tout%20his%20border-control%20plans%20and%20planning%20to%20meet%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20at%20the%20Elysee%20Palace%20in%20the%20coming%20days.%20Labour's%20poll%20lead%20widened%20to%2022%20points%20this%20week%2C%20according%20to%20the%20polling%20firm%20YouGov.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EUK%20Labour%20Leader%20Keir%20Starmer.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20week%20seems%20to%20bring%20more%20reminders%20of%20how%20public%20services%20have%20declined%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20including%20Mr%20Sunak's%20more%20than%20two-year%20tenure%20running%20the%20Treasury.%20The%20government's%20decision%20to%20close%20more%20than%20100%20schools%20over%20overdue%20efforts%20to%20replace%20a%20weak%20type%20of%20concrete%20popular%20in%20the%201960s%20and%201970s%20seemed%20tailor-made%20for%20Labour's%20efforts%20to%20charge%20Mr%20Sunak%20with%20neglect.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20their%20weekly%20face-off%20in%20parliament%2C%20Starmer%20countered%20that%20Mr%20Sunak%20was%20%26quot%3Binaction%20man.%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BEvery%20week%2C%20whatever%20the%20topic%2C%20the%20prime%20minister%20paints%20this%20picture%20as%20if%20everything%20is%20great%20and%20fine%20out%20there.%20It%20is%20so%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20lived%20experience%20in%20the%20real%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20Starmer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDowning%20Street%20aides%20want%20to%20make%20the%20Sunak-Starmer%20showdown%20a%20personality-driven%20presidential%20contest.%20They%20say%20the%20public%20has%20yet%20to%20see%20Mr%20Sunak's%20best%20qualities%20and%20hope%20his%20speech%20at%20the%20Conservative%20conference%20in%20October%20could%20provide%20a%20breakthrough%20moment.%20They're%20hoping%20an%20economic%20turnaround%20next%20year%20could%20provide%20Britons%20some%20relief%20just%20before%20they%20head%20to%20the%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EToo%20Cautious%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStarmer%20could%20face%20his%20own%20challenges%20if%20he%20attempts%20to%20counter%20criticism%20that%20he's%20too%20cautious%20by%20detailing%20how%20he%20would%20handle%20controversial%20issues.%20He%20got%20of%20taste%20of%20that%20this%20week%20as%20right-leaning%20newspapers%20criticized%20Starmer's%20plans%20to%20cut%20migration%20across%20the%20English%20Channel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20some%20of%20Mr%20Sunak's%20own%20planned%20policy%20moves%20-%20such%20as%20potentially%20scaling%20back%20the%20planned%20HS2%20high-speed%20railway%20to%20Manchester%20-%20risk%20further%20alienating%20voters.%20And%20it's%20difficult%20to%20tell%20voters%20to%20not%20look%20back%20when%20long-festering%20problems%20keep%20interrupting%20their%20daily%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20McTernan%2C%20a%20political%20strategist%20and%20former%20adviser%20to%20ex-Labour%20Prime%20Minister%20Tony%20Blair%20and%20Australian%20Premier%20Julia%20Gillard%2C%20said%20the%20prime%20minister%20had%20his%20chance%20to%20make%20a%20clean%20break%20with%20his%20predecessors'%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSunak's%20problem%20is%20that%20you%20only%20get%20one%20chance%20to%20make%20a%20first%20impression%2C%26quot%3B%20McTernan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694843100000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2022-12%2Fu7npb71_rishi-sunak-bloomberg_625x300_12_December_22.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fdont-look-back-hope-for-the-best-rishi-sunaks-plan-to-save-his-job-4394926%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Much%20of%20Westminster%20sniggered%20earlier%20this%20month%20when%20Rishi%20Sunak%20branded%20Keir%20Starmer%20%26quot%3BCaptain%20Hindsight.%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C