ration%20between%20two%20mediation%20powerhouses%20will%20increase%20investor%20confidence%20and%20ensure%20swift%2C%20equitable%20solutions%20for%20sustainable%20commercial%20growth%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fevents-corner%2Fiamc-hyderabad-singapore-international-mediation-centre-mou-maxwell-chambers-236599%5C%22%3Ethe%20IAMC%20registrar%20said%20on%20August%2030%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20SIMC%20secretariat%2C%20Panchu%20has%20alleged%20that%20Justice%20Ramana%20has%20greatly%20damaged%20the%20cause%20of%20mediation%20and%20judicial%20propriety%20by%20starting%2C%20as%20a%20virtually%20private%20venture%2C%20the%20IAMC%20when%20he%20was%20heading%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20judiciary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanchu%20has%20alleged%20that%20the%20Telangana%20state%20government%20gave%20the%20IAMC%20public%20funds%20and%20immovable%20assets%20%E2%80%9Cin%20violation%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20also%20referred%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Flawyers-allege-illegal-acts-in-mediation-centre-founding-seek-action-against-justice-ramana%5C%22%3Ecomplaint%3C%2Fa%3E%20submitted%20last%20year%20by%20over%2060%20mediators%2C%20lawyers%20and%20others%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20the%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20the%20Comptroller%20and%20Auditor%20General%20of%20India%20against%20Ramana%20and%20others%20associated%20with%20him.%20%E2%80%9CProceedings%20have%20begun%20in%20the%20state%20as%20well.%C2%A0%20These%20are%20pending%2C%E2%80%9D%20Panchu%20says%20in%20his%20letter%20to%20the%20SIMS%20secretariat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanchu%20questioned%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20appointment%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Cexpert%20mediator%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20is%20no%20known%20record%20of%20any%20mediations%20conducted%20by%20him%2C%20which%20he%20says%20%E2%80%9Cintrigued%E2%80%9D%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20surprised%2C%20shocked%20and%20saddened%20by%20your%20decision%20to%20associate%20with%20him.%20My%20favourable%20impression%20of%20your%20organisation%20has%20eroded%20considerably%2C%E2%80%9D%20Panchu%20said%20in%20his%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20he%20does%20not%20wish%20to%20be%20on%20any%20panel%20which%20has%20Ramana%20as%20a%20member%2C%20nor%20be%20a%20part%20of%20any%20organisation%20which%20embraces%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20sent%20an%20email%20to%20the%20SIMS%20secretariat%20but%20has%20yet%20to%20receive%20its%20response%20to%20Panchu%E2%80%99s%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Panchu%E2%80%99s%20letter%20to%20the%20SIMC%20only%20refers%20directly%20to%20Justice%20Ramana%20and%20his%20credentials%20as%20a%20mediator%2C%20the%202022%20representation%20he%20appended%20raises%20a%20number%20of%20issues%20surrounding%20the%20former%20CJI%E2%80%99s%20association%20with%20the%20IAMC%20in%20Hyderabad.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F13145326%2FFFwvKrsUYAMLMY7.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F13145326%2FFFwvKrsUYAMLMY7.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F13145326%2FFFwvKrsUYAMLMY7-300x149.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F06%2F13145326%2FFFwvKrsUYAMLMY7-1024x509.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-601297%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22597%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETelangana%20CM%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao%20and%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%20NV%20Ramana%20with%20others%20at%20the%20International%20Arbitration%20and%20Mediation%20Centre%20(IAMC)%20curtain%20raiser%20in%20Hyderabad%20in%20December%202021.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40TelanganaCMO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20signatories%20to%20the%20representation%20urged%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20constitute%20a%20high-level%20committee%20to%20conduct%20an%20inquiry%20into%20what%20they%20alleged%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cillegal%E2%80%9D%20establishment%20of%20the%20IAMC%20and%20the%20transfer%20of%20public%20land%20to%20it.%20They%20also%20asked%20that%20appropriate%20guidelines%20be%20framed%20relating%20to%20the%20conduct%20of%20judges%20while%20in%20office%2C%20restraining%20them%20from%20involving%20themselves%20in%20private%20ventures%20which%20receive%20government%20largesse%20in%20the%20form%20land%20and%20funds.%20They%20also%20said%20that%20there%20had%20been%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act%2C%20which%20penalises%20public%20servants%20(like%20judges)%20for%20accepting%20property%20without%20consideration%20or%20inadequate%20consideration%20%E2%80%93%20in%20this%20instance%2C%20from%20the%20Government%20of%20Telangana%20whose%20cases%20were%20being%20heard%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20IAMC%20was%20inaugurated%20in%20Hyderabad%20on%20December%2018%2C%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Panchu%2C%20it%20was%20virtually%20a%20private%20initiative%20of%20Justice%20Ramana%2C%20who%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Farticle%2Fcurrent-affairs%2Findia-s-first-international-arbitration-and-mediation-centre-opens-in-hyd-121121800768_1.html%5C%22%3Ebroached%20the%20subject%20with%20the%20Telangana%20chief%20minister%20on%20June%2012%2C%202021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20authored%20the%20trust%20deed%20dated%20August%2020%2C%202021%20in%20which%20Justice%20Nageswara%20Rao%20and%20former%20Supreme%20Court%20Judge%2C%20Justice%20R.V.%20Raveendran%20were%20named%20as%20life%20trustees%2C%20and%20the%20then%C2%A0%20Telangana%20Chief%20Justice%2C%20Hima%20Kohli%20(who%20subsequently%20was%20appointed%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court)%20and%20law%20minister%20as%20ex-officio%20trustees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Flawyers-allege-illegal-acts-in-mediation-centre-founding-seek-action-against-justice-ramana%5C%22%3ELawyers%20Allege%20%E2%80%98Illegal%20Acts%E2%80%99%20in%20Mediation%20Centre%20Founding%2C%20Seek%20Action%20Against%20Justice%20Ramana%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJustices%20Nageswara%20Rao%2C%20Raveendran%2C%20Kohli%20and%20current%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20Telangana%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20Alok%20Aradhe%20continue%20to%20be%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiamch.org.in%2Fabout%2Fboard-of-trustees%5C%22%3EBoard%20of%20Trustees%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20IAMC.%C2%A0%20Justices%20Rao%20and%20Raveendran%20are%20part%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiamch.org.in%2Fabout%2Fgoverning-council%5C%22%3EGoverning%20Council%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20IAMC%20as%20well.%20While%20Justices%20Rao%20and%20Raveendran%20are%20life%20trustees%2C%20the%20term%20of%20Justice%20Kohli%20is%20for%20three%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPanchu%E2%80%99s%20allegations%20of%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20judges%20of%20the%20higher%20judiciary%20were%20debated%20last%20year%20in%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fcolumns%2Fbreaking-the-mediation-monopoly-a-reply-to-sriram-panchu-202489%5C%22%3E%20an%20article%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20senior%20advocate%20Gopal%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20who%20defended%20the%20role%20of%20the%20judges%20in%20the%20IAMC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESankaranarayanan%2C%20in%20his%20June%202022%20article%2C%20pointed%20out%20the%20following%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Col%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20IAMC%20is%20set%20up%20as%20a%20public%20trust%20in%20accordance%20with%20the%202017%20Report%20of%20the%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20which%20said%20that%20infrastructural%20support%20ought%20to%20be%20given%20by%20the%20government%20without%20any%20interference%20in%20their%20actual%20functioning.%20A%20parallel%20was%20drawn%20with%20Maxwell%20Chambers%20in%20Singapore.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EClause%204%20of%20the%20trust%20deed%20provides%20that%20there%20will%20be%20two%20life%20trustees%20(Justice%20R.V%20Raveendran%20and%20Justice%20L.%20Nageswara%20Rao)%2C%20two%20ex-officio%20trustees%20and%20three%203-year%20term%20trustees.%20None%20of%20the%20members%20of%20the%20trust%20have%20any%20role%20to%20play%20with%20the%20selection%20of%20arbitrators%20and%20mediators%20and%20none%20of%20them%20can%20be%20appointed%20as%20arbitrators%20or%20mediators%20by%20the%20IAMC.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ENo%20trustee%20receives%20a%20sitting%20fee%20or%20remuneration%20for%20their%20work%20nor%20receives%20compensation%20of%20any%20sort%20from%20the%20IAMC.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMediators%20are%20appointed%20only%20with%20the%20consent%20of%20parties%2C%20and%20if%20this%20is%20not%20possible%2C%20only%20then%20is%20a%20panel%20proposed%20by%20the%20CEO%20in%20consultation%20with%20the%20governing%20council%20%E2%80%93%20the%20trustees%20play%20no%20part.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Fol%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Sankaranarayanan%20ignored%20the%20fact%20that%20two%20trustees%20are%20also%20part%20of%20the%20governing%20council%20and%20may%20thus%20end%20up%20playing%20a%20role%20in%20proposing%20mediators.%20Panchu%2C%20on%20his%20part%2C%20reiterated%20his%20allegations%2C%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdebate-we-need-plain-speaking-to-reaffirm-judicial-values%5C%22%3Erejoinder%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20Sankaranarayanan%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fcolumns%2Fby-all-means-let-it-rain-rain-is-welcome-on-the-entire-mediation-landscape-not-in-select-judicial-enclaves-questionably-acquired-202354%5C%22%3Eanother%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20Justice%20K.%20Kannan%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fcolumns%2Fwhat-the-dark-clouds-bring-just-not-storm-but-rain-202071%5C%22%3Efound%20%3C%2Fa%3Enothing%20wrong%20in%20judges%20setting%20up%20a%20mediation%20centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20light%20of%20Panchu%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20from%20the%20Singapore%20International%20Mediation%20Centre%20citing%20the%20controversy%20over%20the%20IAMC%E2%80%99s%20origins%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20wrote%20to%20the%20SIMC%2C%20Justice%20Ramana%2C%20and%20Justice%20Raveendran%20seeking%20their%20responses%20to%20the%20questions%20that%20had%20been%20raised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECharge%20%E2%80%98factually%20incorrect%E2%80%99%20says%20Justice%20Raveendran%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20their%2022-page%20representation%20sent%20to%20various%20constitutional%20authorities%20in%20August%202022%2C%20the%20signatories%20alleged%20that%20Justice%20Ramana%20included%20Justice%20R.V.%20Raveendran%20as%20a%20life%20trustee%20when%20the%20latter%20was%20enquiring%20into%20a%20matter%20connected%20with%20allegations%20of%20corrupt%20practice%20of%20procuring%20huge%20land%20by%20Justice%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20daughters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Justice%20Raveendran%20has%20denied%20the%20allegation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20no%20truth%20in%20the%20allegation%20that%20Justice%20Ramana%20requested%20me%20to%20be%20a%20life%20trustee%20in%20the%20IAMC%E2%80%99s%20Board%20at%20a%20time%20when%20I%20was%20entrusted%20with%20an%20inquiry%20into%20a%20phone%20conversation%20of%20Justice%20V.Eswaraiah%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Raveendran%20wrote%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20response%20to%20a%20request%20for%20clarification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20noted%20that%20it%20was%20on%20August%2013%2C%202020%2C%20that%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20High%20Court%20directed%20an%20inquiry%20into%20a%20telephone%20conversation%20by%20a%20former%20chief%20justice%20of%20the%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20high%20court%2C%20Justice%20V%20Eswaraiah%2C%20in%20which%20he%20had%20admitted%20that%20he%20was%20%E2%80%9Ctrying%20to%20collect%20more%20evidence%E2%80%9D%20on%20the%20alleged%20involvement%20of%20Justice%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20daughters%20in%20the%20Amaravati%20land%20scam.%20On%20August%2024%2C%20Justice%20Raveendran%20agreed%20to%20head%20the%20inquiry.%20On%20May%2015%2C%202021%2C%20Justice%20Raveendran%20terminated%20and%20closed%20the%20inquiry%20and%20informed%20the%20high%20court%20and%20Justice%20Eswaraiah%20about%20this.%20It%20was%20only%20three%20months%20later%2C%20on%20August%2020%2C%202021%2C%20that%20Justice%20Ramana%20declared%20the%20IAMC%20Trust%2C%20appointing%20Justice%20Raveendran%20and%20Justice%20L.%20Nageswara%20Rao%20as%20life%20trustees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20a%20factually%20incorrect%20statement%20attributed%20to%20Sriram%20Panchu%20is%20now%20sought%20to%20be%20repeated%20in%20a%20totally%20unconnected%20issue%20of%20Sriram%20Panchu%E2%80%99s%20resignation%20from%20the%20mediation%20panel%20of%20SIMC%2C%20following%20the%20inclusion%20of%20Justice%20Ramana%20in%20the%20mediation%20panel%E2%80%9D%2C%20Justice%20Raveendran%20added%20in%20his%20clarification.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPoint%2C%20counterpoint%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20on%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3ERamana%20and%20the%20IAMC%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThough%20Justice%20Ramana%20has%20not%20replied%20to%20the%20email%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20sent%20him%2C%20sources%20in%20the%20IAMC%20responded%20to%20some%20of%20the%20concerns%20raised%2C%20on%20condition%20of%20anonymity.%20Panchu%20also%20agreed%20to%20provide%20his%20responses%20to%20the%20same.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWas%20there%20any%20impropriety%20in%20a%20sitting%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20establishing%20the%20IAMC%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20sources%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20foundation%20for%20the%20IAMC%20is%20a%20public%20charitable%20trust%2C%20which%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20has%20its%20genesis%20in%20the%20recommendations%20of%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20for%20the%20promotion%20of%20institutional%20dispute%20resolution%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20then%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20India%2C%20N%20V%20Ramana%2C%20no%20doubt%2C%20actively%20and%20publicly%20supported%20and%20mentored%20the%20initiative%20for%20setting%20up%20of%20IAMC.%C2%A0%20However%2C%20he%20is%20neither%20a%20Trustee%20nor%20a%20Member%20of%20the%20Governing%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESriram%20P%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eanchu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20What%20is%20so%20public%20about%20the%20IAMC%3F%20It%20is%20created%20by%20an%20individual.%20N.V.%20Ramana%2C%20in%20his%20private%20capacity.%20Three%20trustees%20%E2%80%93%20Justice%20(Retd)%20Nageswara%20Rao%2C%20Justice%20(Retd)%20R.V.%20Raveendran%20and%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli%20serve%20in%20their%20private%20capacity%20as%20appointees%20of%20Ramana.%20Only%20two%20trustees%20are%20ex-officio.%20One%20is%20the%20state%20law%20minister.%20The%20other%20is%20the%20state%20high%20court%20chief%20justice%2C%20and%20it%20is%20high%20time%20he%20reconsidered%20the%20involvement%20of%20his%20high%20office%20in%20this%20controversial%20venture.%20What%20will%20he%20do%20if%20a%20case%20is%20filed%20against%20the%20IAMC%20on%20the%20multiple%20grounds%20that%20are%20available%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Ramana%20has%20no%20leading%20role%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.barandbench.com%2Fnews%2Fjustice-nageswara-rao-head-iamc-hyderabad-cji-ramana%5C%22%3Ehow%20did%20he%20announce%20at%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20Bar%20farewell%20for%20Nageswara%20Rao%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Rao%20is%20going%20to%20take%20over%20as%20the%20next%20chairman%20of%20IAMC%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20and%20why%20did%20Ramana%20visit%20every%20major%20Western%20country%20at%20official%20expense%2C%20in%20each%20place%20emphasising%2C%20falsely%2C%20that%20the%20IAMC%20was%20an%20official%20body%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20and%20thus%20drumming%20up%20business%20for%20it%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20indeed%2C%20if%20he%20had%20no%20formal%20connection%20to%20the%20IAMC%2C%20what%20was%20he%20doing%20receiving%20the%20Memorandum%20of%20Agreement%20from%20the%20SIMC%20Chairman%20on%20September%207%20at%20Singapore%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20there%20a%20conflict%20of%20interest%20in%20a%20sitting%20CJI%20seeking%20and%20accepting%20the%20help%20of%20the%20Telangana%20government%20in%20setting%20up%20the%20IAMC%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20source%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3A%C2%A0%20The%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20Committee%20had%C2%A0%20recommended%20that%20to%20provide%20a%20boost%20to%20institutional%20arbitration%20and%20mediation%20in%20India%2C%20governments%20could%20play%20a%20useful%20role%20by%20providing%20the%20required%20infrastructural%20support%20without%20interfering%20in%20any%20manner%20in%20the%20actual%20functioning%20of%20the%20institution.%20The%20Srikrishna%20committee%20report%20expressly%20noted%20that%20the%20support%20of%20the%20respective%20governments%20was%20a%20significant%20factor%20in%20the%20success%20of%20the%20Singapore%20International%20Arbitration%20Centre%20and%20the%20Hong%20Kong%20International%20Arbitration%20Centre.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20light%20of%20such%20recommendations%2C%20the%20state%20government%20has%20offered%20IAMC%20dedicated%20state-of-the-art%20infrastructure%20and%20has%20provided%20a%20suitable%2C%20rented%20premises%2C%20annual%20grant%20for%20meeting%20the%20expenses%20and%20a%20piece%20of%20land%20for%20housing%20the%20IAMC%E2%80%99s%20facilities.%C2%A0%20The%20land%20has%20not%20been%20allotted%20to%20any%20individual%20and%20is%20entrusted%20to%20the%20trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20government%20of%20Telangana%20initiated%20steps%20for%20setting%20up%20a%20world-class%20arbitration%20centre%20so%20as%20to%20provide%20a%20credible%20facility%20for%20expeditious%20and%20quality%20dispute%20resolution%2C%20as%20envisaged%20by%20the%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20committee%2C%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20faulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESriram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EPanchu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%20Justice%20Srikrishna%20said%20governments%20can%20play%20a%20useful%20role.%20One%20should%20ask%20him%20what%20he%20thinks%20of%20governments%20handing%20over%20Rs%20250%20crore%20of%20land%2C%20reportedly%20Rs%2050%20crore%20for%20construction%20and%20giving%2025%2C000%20sq%20ft%20of%20constructed%20space%20free%20of%20rent%20to%20a%20virtually%20private%20body%20created%20by%20a%20sitting%20judge%20and%20staffed%20with%20sitting%2Fex%20judges%20who%20hear%20cases%20for%20and%20against%20the%20government.%20Undoubtedly%2C%20he%20would%20point%20to%20Section%2011%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20by%20the%20way%2C%20please%20note%20that%20there%20is%20no%20rebuttal%20that%20such%20huge%20public%20assets%20have%20been%20given%20to%20a%20body%20set%20up%20by%20sitting%20judges.%20If%20Ramana%20had%20not%20been%20CJI%2C%20does%20anyone%20expect%20the%20Telangana%20government%20to%20have%20been%20so%20generous%3F%20And%20not%20a%20mention%20of%20how%20this%20is%20not%20a%20fit%20case%20for%20the%20invocation%20of%20the%20Prevention%20of%20Corruption%20Act.%20If%20a%20politician%20had%20done%20this%2C%20he%20would%20have%20been%20out%20of%20office%20in%20a%20jiffy%20and%20facing%20criminal%20charges%20on%20orders%20of%20the%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHave%20the%20appointments%20to%20the%20IAMC%20been%20above%20board%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20source%3A%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20trustees%20of%20the%20IAMC%20are%20two%20retired%20judges%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(life%20trustees)%20viz.%20justice%20R%20V%20Raveendran%20and%20Justice%20L%20Nageswara%20Rao%2C%20a%20sitting%20Judge%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20(term%20trustee)%20Ms.%20Justice%20Hima%20Kohli%2C%20the%20Chief%20Justice%20of%20High%20Court%20of%20Telangana%20(ex-officio%20trustee)%20Justice%20Alok%20Aradhe%20and%20the%20Law%20Minister%20of%20the%20State%20of%20Telangana%20(ex-officio%20trustee)%20Indrakaran%20Reddy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sitting%20and%20retired%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20who%20act%20as%20the%20trustees%20of%20IAMC%20offer%20guidance%20and%20ensure%20that%20the%20centre%20operates%20independently%20without%20any%20external%20influence%20or%20control%20by%20the%20government%20or%20other%20agencies.%C2%A0%20The%20trustees%20serve%20in%20the%20position%20of%20responsibility%20and%20not%20reward.%20None%20of%20the%20trustees%20receive%20any%20sitting%20fee%20or%20remuneration%20for%20their%20work%2C%20it%20is%20learnt.%C2%A0%20None%20of%20the%20trustees%20can%20be%20appointed%20by%20IAMC%20as%20arbitrators%2Fmediators%3B%20the%20trustees%20cannot%20appoint%20anyone%20as%20arbitrator%20or%20mediator.%C2%A0%20The%20trustees%20have%20neither%20received%20nor%20can%20receive%20any%20monetary%20compensation%20or%20benefit%20whatsoever%20from%20the%20Trust%20or%20the%20centre%20for%20performing%20their%20respective%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20two%20life%20trustees%20who%20are%20retired%20Judges%20of%20Supreme%20Court%20also%20serve%20as%20members%20of%20the%20governing%20council.%20The%20members%20of%20the%20governing%20council%20also%20do%20not%20receive%20any%20sitting%20fee%20or%20remuneration%20from%20the%20Centre.%20Members%20of%20the%20governing%20council%20cannot%20be%20appointed%20by%20IAMC%20to%20work%20as%20arbitrators%20or%20mediators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20provisions%2C%20and%20internal%20checks%20and%20balances%2C%20ensure%20that%20the%20IAMC%20operates%20as%20an%20independent%20and%20transparent%20body%2C%20free%20from%20any%20governmental%20or%20other%20control.%20The%20rules%20of%20the%20IAMC%20are%20in%20line%20with%20party%20autonomy%2C%20enabling%20the%20parties%20to%20choose%20the%20arbitrators%20or%20mediators.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESriram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EPanchu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ENo%20one%20objects%20to%20ex-officio%20appointments%20and%20to%20appointments%20made%20by%20a%20proper%20official%20body%2C%20either%20government%20or%20court.%20But%20this%20rather%20shady%20underhand%20business%20is%20galling%2C%20passing%20it%20off%20as%20a%20public%20venture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20been%20the%20IAMC%E2%80%99s%20record%20so%20far%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20sources%3A%20The%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIAMC%20is%20making%20giant%20strides%20in%20capacity%20building%20for%20credible%20institutional%20mediation%20and%20arbitration%20in%20active%20collaboration%20with%20individuals%20and%20organisations%20of%20global%20repute%20in%20the%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPanchu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20existential%20evidence%20for%20the%20IAMC%E2%80%99s%20statement%20is%20doubtful%3B%20some%20knowledgeable%20people%20have%20said%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20much%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20assuming%20it%20to%20be%20so%2C%20when%20you%20have%20such%20facilities%2C%20when%20the%20state%20government%20has%20mandated%20that%20all%20its%20disputes%20come%20to%20you%2C%20when%20Justice%20Ramana%20has%20handpicked%20members%20for%20the%20National%20Company%20Law%20Tribunal%2C%20which%20handles%20the%20biggest%20commercial%20and%20insolvency%20disputes%2C%20the%20work%20you%20are%20getting%20is%20not%20because%20you%20deserve%20it%2C%20but%20because%20litigants%20are%20forced%20your%20way.%20At%20the%20cost%20of%20other%20institutions%20set%20up%20by%20mediators%20across%20the%20country%20who%20have%20slogged%20their%20guts%20out%20for%20many%20years%20to%20make%20mediation%20a%20reality%2C%20but%20see%20the%20fruits%20being%20gobbled%20up%20by%20retired%20judges%20who%20have%20no%20mediation%20capacity%20worth%20the%20name%20but%20are%20willing%20to%20bend%20their%20office%20to%20set%20up%20and%20control%20mediation%20centres.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20Justice%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20qualifications%20to%20be%20a%20mediator%20and%20a%20member%20of%20the%20SIMC%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20source%3A%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EJustice%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20suitability%20as%20a%20mediator%20cannot%C2%A0%20not%20be%20questioned%20because%20he%20was%20a%20judge%20and%20chief%20justice%20for%20more%20than%20two%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELinking%20his%20empanelment%20to%20the%20IAMC%20is%20nothing%20but%20targeting%20the%20IAMC%20by%20invoking%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESriram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EPanchu%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EI%20was%20targeting%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20appointment%2C%20not%20the%20IAMC.%20The%20latter%20is%20no%20doubt%20an%20excellent%20target%20on%20several%20counts%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20for%20another%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20can%E2%80%99t%20possible%20mean%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20a%20quid%20pro%20quo%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20blatant.%20Look%20at%20the%20two%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fandhra-pradesh%2Fformer-cji-nv-ramana-appointed-member-of-international-mediator-panel-of-simc%2Farticle67249309.ece%5C%22%3Eside%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiamch.org.in%2Fiamc-hyderabad-signs-mou-with-singapore-international-mediation-centre%5C%22%3Eside%3C%2Fa%3E%20announcements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20has%20Justice%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20experience%20in%20the%20field%20of%20mediation%20been%20so%20far%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIAMC%20source%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Every%20time%20a%20judge%20withdraws%20to%20his%20chamber%20to%20settle%20a%20family%20dispute%20in-camera%2C%20what%20she%2Fhe%20does%20essentially%20is%20mediation.%20As%20it%20is%20the%20judges%20who%20advise%20from%20the%20bench%20to%20try%20the%20mediation%20route%20in%20certain%20matters%2C%20the%20reference%20for%20mediation%20by%20a%20judge%20is%20not%20done%20without%20them%20understanding%20what%20mediation%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESriram%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EPanchu%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20So%20this%20is%20the%20justification%20for%20SIMC%20to%20appoint%20Ramana%20as%20its%20%E2%80%9Cexpert%20mediator%E2%80%9D%20on%20its%20international%20panel%20%E2%80%93%20no%20mediation%20conducted%20by%20him.%20The%20other%20members%20of%20the%20distinguished%20international%20panel%20and%20the%20SIMC%20Board%20may%20kindly%20take%20note.%20I%20haven%E2%80%99t%20come%20across%20a%20better%20instance%20of%20egg%20on%20the%20face%20of%20an%20institution.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694797909000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15223434%2FThe-Wire-11.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fas-former-cji-ramana-joins-singapore-mediation-centre-sriram-panchu-quits-questions-credentials%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22At%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20controversy%20is%20the%20establishment%20of%20International%20Arbitration%20and%20Mediation%20Centre%20in%20Hyderabad%20last%20year.%20Panchu%20has%20faulted%20Ramana%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20the%20past%20while%20others%20have%20defended%20him.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fas-former-cji-ramana-joins-singapore-mediation-centre-sriram-panchu-quits-questions-credentials%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Contentious%20Election%20Commissioners%20Bill%20on%20Agenda%20for%20Special%20Session%20of%20Parliament%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20listed%20four%20Bills%20for%20consideration%20and%20passage%20in%20the%20upcoming%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20which%20is%20scheduled%20to%20begin%20on%20Monday%2C%20September%2018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20August%2031%2C%20Union%20minister%20for%20parliamentary%20affairs%2C%20Pralhad%20Joshi%2C%20had%20announced%20that%20a%20special%20session%20of%20parliament%20would%20be%20held%20from%20September%2018%20to%2022.%20Joshi%20did%20not%2C%20however%2C%20reveal%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20session.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmid%20mounting%20criticism%20from%20the%20opposition%20around%20the%20%E2%80%9Csecrecy%E2%80%9D%20surrounding%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20special%20session%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20September%2013%2C%20published%20the%20tentative%20agenda%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20Rajya%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20late-night%20bulletin%2C%20the%20government%20listed%20four%20Bills%20for%20consideration%20and%20passage.%20This%20includes%20The%20Advocates%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%3B%20The%20Press%20and%20Registration%20of%20Periodicals%20Bill%2C%202023%3B%20The%20Post%20Office%20Bill%2C%202023%3B%20and%20The%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%2C%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Rajya%20Sabha%E2%80%99s%20parliamentary%20bulletin%2C%20however%2C%20stated%20that%20the%20list%20is%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20to%20be%20taken%20as%20exhaustive.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere%E2%80%99s%20a%20look%20at%20the%20four%20Bills%20that%20have%20been%20listed%20for%20the%20special%20session%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Chief%20Election%20Commissioner%20and%20other%20Election%20Commissioners%20(Appointment%2C%20Conditions%20of%20Service%2C%20Term%20of%20Office)%20Bill%2C%202023%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contentious%20Bill%20which%20has%20raised%20questions%20about%20the%20independence%20of%20the%20election%20commission%20ahead%20of%20the%20general%20elections%20in%202024%2C%20was%20introduced%20on%20August%2010%20by%20the%20Union%20ministry%20for%20law%20and%20justice%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20just%20a%20day%20before%20the%20parliament%E2%80%99s%20monsoon%20session%20was%20to%20draw%20to%20a%20close.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20repeals%20the%20Election%20Commission%20(Conditions%20of%20Service%20of%20Election%20Commissioners%20and%20Transaction%20of%20Business)%20Act%2C%201991.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Article%20324%20of%20the%20constitution%2C%20the%20election%20commission%20will%20consist%20of%20the%20chief%20election%20commissioner%20(CEC)%20and%20such%20number%20of%20other%20election%20commissioners%20(ECs)%20as%20the%20president%20may%20decide.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20are%20appointed%20by%20the%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bill%2C%20while%20keeping%20the%20same%20composition%20of%20the%20election%20commission%2C%20adds%20that%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20will%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20on%20the%20recommendation%20of%20a%20selection%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20the%20selection%20committee%20will%20consist%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20as%20the%20chairperson%3B%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20as%20member%3B%20and%20a%20Union%20cabinet%20minister%20to%20be%20nominated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20also%20as%20a%20member.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%201991%20Act%20stated%20that%20the%20salary%20of%20the%20ECs%20will%20be%20equal%20to%20that%20of%20a%20Supreme%20Court%20judge%2C%20the%20new%20Bill%20states%20that%20the%20salary%2C%20allowance%2C%20and%20service%20conditions%20of%20the%20CEC%20and%20other%20ECs%20will%20be%20the%20same%20as%20that%20of%20the%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20opposition%20has%20accused%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20government%20of%20using%20the%20Bill%20to%20control%20the%20election%20commission%2C%20former%20chief%20election%20commissioners%20have%20raised%20concerns%20about%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fumpire-cannot-be-subordinate-to-team-captain%5C%22%3Edowngrading%20of%20the%20status%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20election%20commissioners%20as%20well%20as%20the%20CEC%20from%20being%20at%20par%20with%20Supreme%20Court%20judges%20to%20that%20of%20cabinet%20secretary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20was%20introduced%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%20just%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fsupreme-court-says-committee-of-pm-leader-of-opposition-cji-should-appoint-election-commissioners%5C%22%3Emonths%20after%20a%20constitution%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruled%20in%20March%20%3C%2Fa%3Ethat%20election%20commissioners%20should%20be%20appointed%20by%20the%20president%20based%20on%20advice%20from%20a%20committee%20comprising%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20the%20leader%20of%20opposition%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20chief%20justice%20of%20India%20(CJI).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Press%20and%20Registration%20of%20Periodicals%20Bill%2C%202023%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20is%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20existing%20Press%20and%20Registration%20of%20Books%20Act%2C%201867%20(PRB)%2C%20and%20was%20passed%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20by%20a%20voice%20vote%20on%20August%203%20in%20the%20Opposition%E2%80%99s%20absence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20provides%20for%20the%20registration%20of%20newspapers%2C%20periodicals%2C%20and%20books%20along%20with%20cataloguing%20of%20books.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20defines%20a%20%E2%80%9Cperiodical%E2%80%9D%20as%20any%20publication%2C%C2%A0%20including%20a%20newspaper%2C%20which%20is%20published%20and%20printed%20at%20regular%20intervals%20containing%20public%20news%20or%20comments%20on%20public%20news%2C%20but%20does%20not%20include%20a%20book%2C%20or%20a%20journal%20including%20a%20book%20or%20journal%20of%20scientific%2C%20technical%20and%20academic%20nature.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20states%20that%20every%20printer%20of%20a%20periodical%20will%20have%20to%20inform%20the%20Press%20Registrar%20General%20(%20through%20an%20online%20portal)%20and%20the%20local%20District%20Magistrate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Section%204(1)%20the%20Bill%20states%20that%20those%20persons%20who%20have%20been%20convicted%20for%20an%20offence%20%E2%80%9Cinvolving%20terrorist%20act%20or%20unlawful%20activity%3B%20or%20for%20having%20done%20anything%20against%20the%20security%20of%20the%20State%E2%80%9D%20will%20not%20be%20allowed%20to%20bring%20out%20a%20periodical.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20provides%20for%20the%20central%20government%20to%20appoint%20a%20Press%20Registrar%20General%20who%20will%20maintain%20a%20register%20of%20newspapers%2C%20issue%20registrations%20to%20periodicals%20and%20will%20also%20have%20the%20power%20to%20revise%2C%20cancel%20or%20suspend%20such%20registrations%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Press%20Registrar%20General%20can%20suspend%20a%20periodical%E2%80%99s%20registration%20for%20a%20minimum%20period%20of%2030%20days%20which%20can%20extend%20to%20180%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESuch%20registrations%20can%20be%20suspended%20due%20to%20false%20information%20provided%20to%20register%20the%20periodical%2C%20failure%20to%20publish%20the%20periodical%20continuously%2C%20giving%20false%20annual%20statements.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20registration%20may%20also%20be%20cancelled%20if%20a%20periodical%20has%20the%20same%20or%20similar%20title%20as%20any%20other%20periodical%2C%20or%20if%20the%20owner%2F%20publisher%20has%20been%20convicted%20of%20a%20terrorist%20act%20or%20unlawful%20activity%2C%20or%20for%20acting%20against%20the%20security%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Editors%20Guild%20of%20India%20has%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fmedia%2Feditors-guild-calls-press-and-registration-of-periodicals-bill-deeply-distressing%5C%22%3Eraised%20concerns%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20the%20bill%20and%20said%20that%20the%20new%20legislation%20%E2%80%9Cwidens%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20to%20have%20more%20intrusive%20and%20arbitrary%20checks%E2%80%9D%20in%20how%20a%20publication%20functions%2C%20adding%20that%20some%20of%20the%20provisions%20were%20%E2%80%9Cvague%E2%80%9D%20and%20the%20ambiguity%20could%20have%20%E2%80%9Cadverse%20implications%20on%20press%20freedom%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%C2%A0The%20Post%20Office%20Bill%2C%202023%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20repeals%20the%20Indian%20Post%20Office%20Act%2C%201898%20and%20provides%20for%20matters%20related%20to%20the%20functioning%20of%20the%20Post%20Office%2C%20an%20undertaking%20of%20the%20central%20government%20(also%20known%20as%20India%20Post).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20allows%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fnew-post-office-bill-employees-open-detain-parcels%5C%22%3Eemployees%20to%20open%20postal%20parcels%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20national%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20public%20security.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20an%20analysis%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Fbilltrack%2Fthe-post-office-bill-2023%5C%22%3EPRS%20Legislative%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20while%20the%20earlier%20Act%20provided%20for%20the%20interception%20of%20a%20shipment%20due%20to%20any%20public%20emergency%2C%20or%20in%20the%20interest%20of%20public%20safety%20or%20tranquillity%20by%20the%20central%20government%2C%20state%20governments%2C%20or%20any%20officer%20specially%20authorised%20by%20them%3B%20the%20new%20bill%20states%20that%20the%20interception%20of%20a%20shipment%20can%20be%20done%20due%20to%20concerns%20relating%20to%20security%20of%20the%20state%2C%20friendly%20relations%20with%20foreign%20states%2C%20public%20order%2C%20emergency%2C%20or%20public%20safety%2C%20and%20contravention%20of%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20or%20any%20other%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20states%20that%20an%20officer%20empowered%20by%20the%20central%20government%20through%20a%20notification%20may%20carry%20out%20an%20interception.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Act%20provided%20for%20an%20officer%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20Post%20Office%20who%20may%20examine%20a%20shipment%20in%20case%20of%20any%20suspicion%20relating%20to%20goods%20which%20are%20prohibited%2C%20or%20those%20that%20may%20be%20liable%20to%20be%20paid%20duty%20upon%20Bill%20does%20away%20with%20this%20process%20of%20examination.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%2C%20the%20Bill%20provides%20that%20in%20such%20cases%2C%20the%20central%20government%20may%20empower%20an%20officer%20of%20the%20Post%20Office%20to%20send%20the%20shipment%20to%20the%20customs%20authority%20or%20any%20other%20specified%20authority%20which%20will%20then%20deal%20with%20the%20item%20in%20question.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20also%20allows%20post%20offices%20to%20have%20the%20exclusive%20privilege%20to%20issue%20postage%20stamps.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Advocates%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Advocates%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%20amends%20the%20Advocates%20Act%2C%201961%20and%20was%20passed%20by%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20on%20August%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FAdvocates%2520(Amendment)%2520Bill%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3Eprovides%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20every%20High%20Court%2C%20District%20Judge%2C%20Sessions%20Judge%2C%20District%20Magistrate%2C%20and%20every%20Revenue-officer%2C%20not%20being%20below%20the%20rank%20of%20a%20Collector%20of%20a%20district%20may%20frame%20and%20publish%20lists%20of%20persons%20who%20act%20as%20touts%2C%20and%20may%2C%20from%20time%20to%20time%2C%20alter%20and%20amend%20such%20lists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETouts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprsindia.org%2Ffiles%2Fbills_acts%2Fbills_parliament%2F2023%2FAdvocates%2520(Amendment)%2520Bill%2C%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3Erefers%20%3C%2Fa%3Eto%20a%20person%20who%20in%20return%20for%20a%20payment%20procures%20or%20proposes%20to%20procure%20the%20employment%20of%20any%20legal%20practitioner%20in%20a%20legal%20business%20or%C2%A0%20who%20for%20the%20purposes%20of%20such%20procurement%20frequents%20the%20precincts%20of%20Civil%20or%20Criminal%20Courts%20or%20of%20revenue-offices%2C%20or%20railway%20stations%2C%20landing%20stages%2C%20lodging%20places%20or%20other%20places%20of%20public%20resort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%20states%20that%20anyone%20who%20acts%20as%20a%20tout%20while%20his%20name%20is%20included%20in%20the%20list%20of%20touts%20framed%20by%20authorities%20will%20be%20punished%20with%20imprisonment%20up%20to%20three%20months%2C%20a%20fine%20up%20to%20Rs%20500%2C%20or%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDiscussion%20on%2075%20years%20of%20parliamentary%20journey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20these%20four%20Bills%2C%20the%20centre%20has%20stated%20in%20its%20parliamentary%20bulletin%20announcing%20the%20agenda%20of%20the%20session%2C%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20discussion%20on%20%E2%80%9CParliamentary%20Journey%20of%2075%20Years%20starting%20from%20Samvidhan%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20Achievements%2C%20Experiences%2C%20Memories%20and%20Learning%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20the%20notices%20for%20the%20tentative%20list%20of%20house%20business%20for%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20and%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20state%20that%20the%20special%20session%20on%20Monday%20will%20include%20this%20discussion%2C%20apart%20from%20the%20normal%20business%20of%20the%20house.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20while%20announcing%20the%20special%20session%2C%20Joshi%20in%20his%20tweet%20on%20X%20(formerly%20Twitter)%20had%20also%20mentioned%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20focus%20on%20Amrit%20Kaal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%20data-width%3D%5C%22550%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-dnt%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESpecial%20Session%20of%20Parliament%20