ews%2Faxis-bank-investment-banking-unit-s-co-ceo-chirag-negandhi-resigns-123091501114_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Faxis-bank-investment-banking-unit-s-co-ceo-chirag-negandhi-resigns-123091501114_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Habitual%20Non-Compliant%20Platform'%3A%20Centre's%20Latest%20Affidavit%20in%20Legal%20Tussle%20with%20X%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15203648%2FThe-Wire-10.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%20called%20X-Corp%20(formerly%2C%20Twitter)%20a%20%E2%80%9Chabitual%20non-compliant%20platform%E2%80%9D%20in%20its%20latest%20court%20filing%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20ongoing%20legal%20tussle%20between%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20and%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20details%20about%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20latest%20affidavit%20%E2%80%93%20filed%20before%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20on%20August%2024%20%E2%80%93%20came%20to%20light%20after%20the%20news%20agency%20Reuters%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Findia%2Findia-calls-x-habitual-non-compliant-platform-latest-court-tussle-2023-09-13%2F%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20story%20based%20on%20its%20contents%20earlier%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CX-Corp%20does%20not%20follow%20the%20law%20of%20the%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20this%20lowered%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20authority%20of%20the%20law%2C%20judiciary%2C%20and%20executive%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20filing%20is%20in%20response%20to%20X-Corp%E2%80%99s%20appeal%20before%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%2C%20challenging%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20June%20verdict%20where%20it%20had%20dismissed%20the%20social%20media%20platform%E2%80%99s%20challenge%20questioning%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20orders%20to%20block%20certain%20accounts%20and%20posts.%20The%20appeal%20by%20X-Corp%20is%20also%20challenging%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20direction%20which%20imposed%20a%20penalty%20of%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20against%20it%20for%20not%20complying%20with%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20orders%20for%20over%20a%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20filing%2C%20which%20runs%20into%2028%20pages%2C%20urges%20the%20court%20to%20dismiss%20X-Corp%E2%80%99s%20appeal%2C%20observing%20that%20the%20company%20has%20undermined%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20role%20of%20the%20government%20in%20a%20democratic%20setup%E2%80%9D.%20It%20has%20also%20alleged%20that%20the%20social%20media%20platform%20had%20in%20the%20past%20unblocked%20some%20accounts%20without%20its%20knowledge%20even%20after%20orders%20were%20issued%20calling%20to%20block%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20goes%20on%20to%20charge%20X-Corp%2C%20saying%20that%20its%20%E2%80%9Ccompliance%20rates%20with%20government%20requests%20have%20been%20significantly%20low%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20the%20duty%20of%20the%20government%20to%20ensure%20that%20platforms%20are%20doing%20business%20in%20a%20legally%20compliant%20manner%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20Information%20Technology%20(IT)%20ministry%20said%20in%20the%20affidavit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX-Corp%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20have%20been%20at%20loggerheads%20since%202o21%20when%20the%20former%20refused%20to%20block%20certain%20accounts%20related%20to%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests.%20The%20government%20issued%20takedown%20orders%20against%20accounts%20which%20it%20deemed%20supportive%20of%20the%20Khalistani%20movement%2C%20posts%20which%20allegedly%20spread%20misinformation%20about%20farmers%E2%80%99%20protests%2C%20and%20also%20those%20critical%20of%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20handling%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20battle%20between%20X-Corp%20and%20the%20Modi%20government%20goes%20back%20to%202021%20before%20the%20platform%20was%20taken%20over%20by%20Elon%20Musk%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20affidavit%20makes%20it%20clear%20that%20compliance%20with%20Indian%20laws%20cannot%20be%20seen%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Coption%20or%20hurdle%20to%20business%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20warned%20the%20platform%20that%20it%20could%20end%20up%20losing%C2%A0protection%20and%20attract%20penal%20action.%20The%20protection%2C%20that%20the%20government%20refers%20to%2C%20is%20related%20to%20the%20immunity%20the%20platform%20enjoys%20as%20an%20intermediary%20for%20the%20content%20posted%20by%20users%2C%20allowing%20it%20to%20take%20refuge%20under%20%E2%80%9Csafe%20harbour%E2%80%9D%20protection%20given%20in%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccusing%20the%20platform%20of%20%E2%80%9Cadvocating%20a%20dangerous%20trend%E2%80%9D%20by%20seeking%20to%20judge%20the%20merits%20of%20government%20orders%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20said%20that%20such%20a%20situation%20could%20make%20all%20platforms%20the%20%E2%80%9Cfinal%20arbitrator%20of%20lawful%20orders%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694790589000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F15203648%2FThe-Wire-10.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhabitual-non-complaint-platform-centres-latest-affidavit-in-legal-tussle-with-x%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20government's%20filing%20urges%20the%20Karnataka%20high%20court%20to%20dismiss%20X-Corp's%20appeal%2C%20observing%20that%20the%20company%20has%20undermined%20'the%20role%20of%20the%20government%20in%20a%20democratic%20setup'.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fhabitual-non-complaint-platform-centres-latest-affidavit-in-legal-tussle-with-x%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%E2%80%8BVijay%20Sethupathi%20is%20a%20versatile%20genius%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22p